1
00:01:16,742 --> 00:01:20,496
<i>GANDALF'. You cannot pass!
FRODO'. Gandalf!</i>

2
00:01:25,334 --> 00:01:30,673
<i>GANDALF'. I am a servant of the Secret Fire,
wielder of the flame of Anor.</i>

3
00:01:38,639 --> 00:01:41,392
<i>Go back to the Shadow.</i>

4
00:01:42,310 --> 00:01:46,105
<i>The dark fire will not avail you,
ﬂame of Ude!</i>

5
00:01:49,942 --> 00:01:54,530
You shall not pass!

6
00:02:00,453 --> 00:02:02,038
[ROARING]

7
00:02:16,218 --> 00:02:18,054
[GRUNTS]

8
00:02:21,641 --> 00:02:23,351
BOROMIR:
No! No!

9
00:02:23,559 --> 00:02:25,561
Gandalf!

10
00:02:33,069 --> 00:02:34,820
Fly, you fools.

11
00:02:35,446 --> 00:02:37,323
No!

12
00:02:39,283 --> 00:02:41,369
Gandalf!

13
00:02:57,468 --> 00:03:01,597
[ROARING AND YELLING]

14
00:03:50,020 --> 00:03:51,856
Gandalf!

15
00:03:52,857 --> 00:03:55,151
What is it, Mr. Frodo?

16
00:03:57,027 --> 00:03:58,779
Nothing.

17
00:04:06,078 --> 00:04:08,164
Just a dream.

18
00:04:21,302 --> 00:04:22,511
Can you see the bottom?

19
00:04:23,804 --> 00:04:26,932
No! Don't look down, Sam!
Just keep going!

20
00:04:33,689 --> 00:04:35,775
[GRUNTS]

21
00:04:37,735 --> 00:04:39,904
Catch it! Grab it, Mr. Frodo!

22
00:04:41,530 --> 00:04:42,782
[YELLS]

23
00:04:42,990 --> 00:04:44,950
Mr. Frodo!

24
00:04:47,536 --> 00:04:49,288
I think I've found the bottom.

25
00:04:54,710 --> 00:04:57,671
SAM: Bogs and rope,
and goodness knows what.

26
00:04:57,838 --> 00:05:01,091
It's not natural. None of it.

27
00:05:04,261 --> 00:05:06,347
-What's in this?
-Nothing.

28
00:05:07,723 --> 00:05:08,766
Just a bit of seasoning.

29
00:05:09,350 --> 00:05:12,228
I thought maybe if we was having
a roast chicken one night or something.

30
00:05:12,728 --> 00:05:14,897
Roast chicken?!

31
00:05:15,523 --> 00:05:16,774
You never know.

32
00:05:17,233 --> 00:05:20,236
<i>Sam. My dear Sam.</i>

33
00:05:21,862 --> 00:05:25,825
It's very special, that.
It's the best salt in all the Shire.

34
00:05:27,076 --> 00:05:29,078
It is special.

35
00:05:32,957 --> 00:05:34,875
It's a little bit of home.

36
00:05:38,170 --> 00:05:40,589
We can't leave this here for someone
to follow us down.

37
00:05:41,048 --> 00:05:44,552
Who's gonna follow us down here,
Mr. Frodo?

38
00:05:45,386 --> 00:05:49,265
It's a shame, really.
Lady Galadriel gave me that.

39
00:05:49,890 --> 00:05:51,851
Real Elvish rope.

40
00:05:52,768 --> 00:05:55,145
Well, there's nothing for it.
It's one of my knots.

41
00:05:55,312 --> 00:05:57,273
Won't come free in a hurry.

42
00:06:06,282 --> 00:06:08,367
Real Elvish rope.

43
00:06:22,464 --> 00:06:26,969
Mordor. The one place in Middle-earth
we don't want to see any closer.

44
00:06:27,136 --> 00:06:29,346
And it's the one place
we're trying to get to.

45
00:06:30,097 --> 00:06:31,849
It's just where we can't get.

46
00:06:33,309 --> 00:06:36,312
Let's face it, Mr. Frodo, we're lost.

47
00:06:38,606 --> 00:06:41,358
I don't think Gandalf meant for us to
come this way.

48
00:06:42,985 --> 00:06:46,322
He didn't mean for a lot of things
to happen, <i>Sam...</i>

49
00:06:47,114 --> 00:06:48,616
...but they did.

50
00:06:55,331 --> 00:06:57,958
[RUMBLING]

51
00:06:58,125 --> 00:07:00,502
[GASPING]

52
00:07:01,670 --> 00:07:02,713
Mr. Frodo?

53
00:07:06,634 --> 00:07:08,052
It's the Ring, isn't it?

54
00:07:09,136 --> 00:07:11,639
It's getting heavier.

55
00:07:24,234 --> 00:07:26,987
-What food have we got left?
-Let me see.

56
00:07:27,696 --> 00:07:29,782
Oh, yes. Lovely.

57
00:07:29,949 --> 00:07:32,701
Lembas bread. And look!

58
00:07:35,162 --> 00:07:37,414
More Iembas bread.

59
00:07:48,175 --> 00:07:50,135
I don't usually hold with foreign food...

60
00:07:50,386 --> 00:07:53,305
...but this Elvish stuff, it's not bad.

61
00:07:54,181 --> 00:07:57,685
Nothing ever dampens your spirits,
does it, Sam?

62
00:08:03,524 --> 00:08:05,818
Those rain clouds might.

63
00:08:09,279 --> 00:08:11,740
[THUNDER ROLLING]

64
00:08:40,060 --> 00:08:42,855
SAM:
This looks strangely familiar.

65
00:08:43,439 --> 00:08:45,941
It's because we've been here before.

66
00:08:46,108 --> 00:08:48,694
We're going in circles.

67
00:08:49,445 --> 00:08:51,280
SAM:
What is that horrid stink?

68
00:08:51,447 --> 00:08:53,657
I warrant there's a nasty bog nearby.

69
00:08:53,824 --> 00:08:55,743
-Can you smell it?
-Yes.

70
00:08:57,786 --> 00:09:00,039
I can smell it.

71
00:09:03,292 --> 00:09:05,753
We're not alone.

72
00:09:19,391 --> 00:09:23,479
The thieves. The thieves.

73
00:09:23,645 --> 00:09:27,608
The filthy little thieves.

74
00:09:28,275 --> 00:09:30,444
Where is it?

75
00:09:30,611 --> 00:09:33,322
Where is it?

76
00:09:33,989 --> 00:09:37,242
They stole it from us.

77
00:09:37,409 --> 00:09:41,622
My precious.

78
00:09:42,498 --> 00:09:45,751
Curse them, we hates them!

79
00:09:45,918 --> 00:09:50,005
It's ours, it is, and we wants it!

80
00:09:50,380 --> 00:09:53,217
[YELLING]

81
00:10:30,212 --> 00:10:32,548
[SAM YELLS]

82
00:10:45,060 --> 00:10:46,854
This is Sting.

83
00:10:47,062 --> 00:10:48,564
You've seen it before...

84
00:10:48,730 --> 00:10:51,233
...haven't you, GOLLUM?

85
00:10:55,279 --> 00:10:58,782
Release him or I'll cut your throat.

86
00:11:00,909 --> 00:11:02,661
[SIGHS]

87
00:11:04,788 --> 00:11:07,374
[WHIMPERS]

88
00:11:10,294 --> 00:11:12,171
[GOLLUM SCREAMING]

89
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:16,633
It burns!

90
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:19,094
It burns us!

91
00:11:20,596 --> 00:11:22,097
It freezes!

92
00:11:23,849 --> 00:11:26,101
Nasty Elves twisted it.

93
00:11:26,268 --> 00:11:28,937
-Take it off us!
—Quiet, you!

94
00:11:32,357 --> 00:11:36,612
It's hopeless. Every Orc in Mordor's
going to hear this racket.

95
00:11:36,778 --> 00:11:39,406
-Let's just tie him up and leave him.
-No!

96
00:11:39,656 --> 00:11:43,160
That would kill us! Kill us!

97
00:11:43,327 --> 00:11:46,038
It's no more than you deserve!

98
00:11:47,706 --> 00:11:49,750
Maybe he does deserve to die.

99
00:11:52,127 --> 00:11:55,631
But now that I see him, I do pity him.

100
00:11:59,051 --> 00:12:03,931
We be nice to them
if they be nice to us.

101
00:12:04,181 --> 00:12:06,934
Take it off us.

102
00:12:10,062 --> 00:12:13,982
We swears to do what you wants.

103
00:12:14,149 --> 00:12:16,151
We swears.

104
00:12:16,401 --> 00:12:18,820
There's no promise you can make
that I can trust.

105
00:12:21,490 --> 00:12:23,283
We swears...

106
00:12:23,492 --> 00:12:28,247
...to serve the master
of the precious.

107
00:12:29,873 --> 00:12:32,209
We will swear on...

108
00:12:32,376 --> 00:12:34,336
...on the precious.

109
00:12:34,503 --> 00:12:36,713
GOLLUM. GOLLUM.

110
00:12:36,880 --> 00:12:41,009
The Ring is treacherous.
It will hold you to your word.

111
00:12:41,843 --> 00:12:43,178
Yes...

112
00:12:43,762 --> 00:12:46,265
...on the precious.

113
00:12:48,684 --> 00:12:51,061
On the precious.

114
00:12:52,229 --> 00:12:53,730
I don't believe you!

115
00:12:55,732 --> 00:12:59,236
-Get down! I said, down!
-Sam!

116
00:12:59,444 --> 00:13:01,154
He's trying to trick us.

117
00:13:01,321 --> 00:13:04,366
If we let him go, he'll throttle us
in our sleep.

118
00:13:04,533 --> 00:13:07,035
[WHEEZING]

119
00:13:15,794 --> 00:13:20,340
-You know the way to Mordor?
-Yes.

120
00:13:23,260 --> 00:13:25,012
You've been there before?

121
00:13:26,013 --> 00:13:27,597
Yes.

122
00:13:38,483 --> 00:13:41,111
You will lead us to the Black Gate.

123
00:13:49,745 --> 00:13:53,540
SMEAGOL: To the Gate, to the Gate!
To the Gate, the master says. Yes!

124
00:13:53,749 --> 00:13:58,545
GOLLUM: No! We won't go back.
Not there. Not to him.

125
00:13:58,754 --> 00:14:03,008
They can't make us. GOLLUM! GOLLUM!

126
00:14:03,175 --> 00:14:06,636
But we swore to serve the master
of the precious.

127
00:14:06,803 --> 00:14:12,768
No. Ashes and dust and thirst there is,
and pits, pits, pits.

128
00:14:12,934 --> 00:14:15,812
And Orcses, thousands of Orcses.

129
00:14:15,979 --> 00:14:21,109
And always the Great Eye watching,
watching.

130
00:14:24,071 --> 00:14:27,908
Hey! Come back now! Come back!

131
00:14:30,285 --> 00:14:32,537
There! What did I tell you?

132
00:14:32,704 --> 00:14:34,915
He's run off, the old villain.

133
00:14:35,082 --> 00:14:37,626
So much for his promises.

134
00:14:37,793 --> 00:14:39,419
SMEAGOL:
This way, Hobbits.

135
00:14:39,628 --> 00:14:41,713
Follow me!

136
00:14:55,519 --> 00:14:56,937
PIPPIN:
Merry!

137
00:14:57,896 --> 00:14:59,398
Merry!

138
00:15:04,945 --> 00:15:08,740
You're late.
Our master grows impatient.

139
00:15:08,907 --> 00:15:10,742
He wants the Shire-rats now.

140
00:15:11,576 --> 00:15:16,164
I don't take orders from Ore-maggots.

141
00:15:17,207 --> 00:15:20,293
Saruman will have his prize.

142
00:15:20,460 --> 00:15:23,630
We will deliver them.

143
00:15:29,845 --> 00:15:31,221
Merry!

144
00:15:31,972 --> 00:15:33,723
Merry? Wake up.

145
00:15:37,185 --> 00:15:39,062
My friend is sick.

146
00:15:39,479 --> 00:15:42,149
He needs water. Please!

147
00:15:42,899 --> 00:15:46,862
Sick, is he?
Give him some medicine, boys!

148
00:15:47,028 --> 00:15:48,989
[LAUGHING]

149
00:15:50,073 --> 00:15:51,741
Stop it!

150
00:15:53,952 --> 00:15:56,580
Can't take his draught!

151
00:15:59,249 --> 00:16:01,877
-Leave him alone!
—Why?

152
00:16:02,377 --> 00:16:05,297
You want some? Huh?

153
00:16:05,505 --> 00:16:08,884
Then keep your mouth shut.

154
00:16:12,304 --> 00:16:14,389
Merry.

155
00:16:15,182 --> 00:16:16,725
Hello, Pip.

156
00:16:18,518 --> 00:16:20,979
-You're hurt.
-I'm fine.

157
00:16:21,146 --> 00:16:23,690
-It was just an act.
-An act?

158
00:16:24,316 --> 00:16:27,194
See? I fooled you too.

159
00:16:29,905 --> 00:16:31,615
Don't worry about me, Pippin.

160
00:16:33,909 --> 00:16:35,911
What is it? What do you smell?

161
00:16:36,912 --> 00:16:38,205
Man-flesh.

162
00:16:40,332 --> 00:16:42,709
They've picked up our trail.

163
00:16:43,793 --> 00:16:44,920
Aragorn.

164
00:16:46,630 --> 00:16:48,465
Let's move!

165
00:17:09,819 --> 00:17:11,905
[RUMBLING]

166
00:17:12,072 --> 00:17:14,574
Their pace has quickened.

167
00:17:15,575 --> 00:17:17,577
They must have caught our scent.

168
00:17:17,744 --> 00:17:19,496
Hurry!

169
00:17:23,124 --> 00:17:24,960
Come on, Gimli!

170
00:17:28,713 --> 00:17:31,007
Three days and nights pursuit.

171
00:17:31,174 --> 00:17:34,135
No food. No rest.

172
00:17:34,302 --> 00:17:38,306
And no sign of our quarry,
but What bare rock can tell.

173
00:18:09,754 --> 00:18:13,008
Not idly do the leaves of Lérien fall.

174
00:18:14,301 --> 00:18:16,636
They may yet be alive.

175
00:18:17,512 --> 00:18:20,140
Less than a day ahead of us. Come.

176
00:18:22,726 --> 00:18:25,228
Come, Gimli! We're gaining on them!

177
00:18:25,395 --> 00:18:29,691
I'm wasted on cross-country.
We Dwarves are natural sprinters.

178
00:18:30,191 --> 00:18:33,528
Very dangerous over short distances.

179
00:18:45,206 --> 00:18:46,958
ARAGORN:
Rohan.

180
00:18:47,125 --> 00:18:49,919
Home of the Horse-lords.

181
00:18:51,129 --> 00:18:53,673
There's something strange at work here.

182
00:18:53,840 --> 00:18:56,843
Some evil gives speed
to these creatures.

183
00:18:57,052 --> 00:18:59,971
Sets its will against us.

184
00:19:05,185 --> 00:19:08,063
ARAGORN:
Legolas! What do your Elf-eyes see?

185
00:19:08,229 --> 00:19:10,815
LEGOLAS:
The Uruks turn northeast.

186
00:19:11,650 --> 00:19:13,818
They are taking the Hobbits to Isengard.

187
00:19:14,694 --> 00:19:15,945
Saruman.

188
00:19:24,371 --> 00:19:27,540
SARU MAN:
<i>The world is changing.</i>

189
00:19:27,707 --> 00:19:33,338
<i>Who now has the strength to stand
against the armies of Isengard...</i>

190
00:19:34,005 --> 00:19:36,758
<i>...and Mordor?</i>

191
00:19:38,426 --> 00:19:44,057
<i>To stand against the might of Sauron
and Saruman...</i>

192
00:19:44,224 --> 00:19:47,894
<i>...and the union of the two towers?</i>

193
00:19:54,401 --> 00:19:57,362
<i>Together, my Lord Sauron...</i>

194
00:19:57,529 --> 00:20:01,116
<i>...We shall rule this Middle-earth.</i>

195
00:20:11,334 --> 00:20:13,211
[YELLING AND SQUEALING]

196
00:20:17,132 --> 00:20:21,386
SARU MAN: <i>The Old World will burn
in the fires of industry.</i>

197
00:20:21,928 --> 00:20:25,223
<i>The forests will fall.</i>

198
00:20:27,142 --> 00:20:29,978
<i>A new order will rise.</i>

199
00:20:31,062 --> 00:20:35,942
<i>We will drive the machine of war
with the sword and the spear...</i>

200
00:20:36,151 --> 00:20:40,155
<i>...and the iron ﬁsts of the Orc.</i>

201
00:20:52,584 --> 00:20:55,795
SARUMAN: I want them armed
and ready to march within two weeks!

202
00:20:55,962 --> 00:20:57,630
ORC:
But, my lord, there are too many!

203
00:20:57,797 --> 00:21:00,800
We cannot all be armed in time,
we don't have the means.

204
00:21:00,967 --> 00:21:04,179
Build a dam, block the stream,
work the furnaces night and day.

205
00:21:04,763 --> 00:21:07,182
We don't have enough fuel
to feed the fires.

206
00:21:08,475 --> 00:21:12,771
The Forest of Fangorn
lies on our doorstep.

207
00:21:14,189 --> 00:21:16,524
-Burn it.
-Yes.

208
00:21:17,233 --> 00:21:19,527
WILD MAN:
We will fight for you.

209
00:21:19,694 --> 00:21:21,696
Swear it.

210
00:21:32,207 --> 00:21:36,961
We will die for Saruman.

211
00:21:38,046 --> 00:21:40,048
SARUMAN:
The Horse-Men took your lands.

212
00:21:40,215 --> 00:21:44,761
They drove your people into the hills
to scratch a living off rocks.

213
00:21:44,928 --> 00:21:46,346
Murderers!

214
00:21:47,263 --> 00:21:49,390
SARUMAN:
Take back the lands they stole from you.

215
00:21:49,557 --> 00:21:51,351
Burn every village!

216
00:21:51,643 --> 00:21:54,103
[YELLING]

217
00:21:54,562 --> 00:21:59,734
SARUMAN: <i>We have only to
remove those who oppose us.</i>

218
00:22:00,235 --> 00:22:02,779
<i>It will begin in Rohan.</i>

219
00:22:03,530 --> 00:22:07,033
<i>Too long have these peasants
stood against you.</i>

220
00:22:07,242 --> 00:22:09,035
<i>But no more.</i>

221
00:22:09,244 --> 00:22:11,454
Eothain! Eothain!

222
00:22:13,623 --> 00:22:16,292
You take your sister.
You'll go faster with just two.

223
00:22:16,668 --> 00:22:19,337
FREDA:
Papa says Eothain must not ride Garulf.

224
00:22:19,504 --> 00:22:21,172
He is too big for him.

225
00:22:21,339 --> 00:22:24,342
Listen to me. You must ride to Edoras
and raise the alarm.

226
00:22:24,509 --> 00:22:27,053
-Do you understand me?
-Yes, Mama.

227
00:22:27,303 --> 00:22:30,223
I don't want to leave.
I don't want to go, Mama.

228
00:22:30,390 --> 00:22:34,102
Freda, I will find you there.

229
00:22:34,269 --> 00:22:35,812
[SCREAMING]

230
00:22:39,023 --> 00:22:40,775
Quickly!

231
00:22:47,115 --> 00:22:48,700
Go, child.

232
00:23:01,546 --> 00:23:03,548
SARU MAN:
<i>Rohan, my lord...</i>

233
00:23:03,965 --> 00:23:06,718
<i>...is ready to fall.</i>

234
00:23:06,926 --> 00:23:07,093
[THUNDER ROLLING]

235
00:23:07,093 --> 00:23:09,178
[THUNDER ROLLING]

236
00:23:12,599 --> 00:23:15,059
[HOOVES BEATING]

237
00:23:17,937 --> 00:23:19,480
Théod red.

238
00:23:19,689 --> 00:23:21,316
Find the king's son!

239
00:23:37,749 --> 00:23:43,838
-Mordor will pay for this.
-These Orcs are not from Mordor.

240
00:23:44,672 --> 00:23:47,508
My Lord Eomer, over here!

241
00:23:56,351 --> 00:23:58,019
He's alive.

242
00:24:28,967 --> 00:24:31,052
Théod red.

243
00:24:44,399 --> 00:24:47,443
EOWYN:
Your son is badly wounded, my lord.

244
00:24:47,902 --> 00:24:50,405
He was ambushed by Orcs.

245
00:24:51,906 --> 00:24:55,535
If we don't defend our country,
Saruman will take it by force.

246
00:24:55,910 --> 00:24:58,413
That is a lie.

247
00:25:00,581 --> 00:25:05,461
Saruman the White has ever been
our friend and ally.

248
00:25:07,088 --> 00:25:09,132
THEODEN:
Grima.

249
00:25:10,550 --> 00:25:12,468
Grima.

250
00:25:15,013 --> 00:25:16,556
Grima.

251
00:25:17,306 --> 00:25:20,435
Orcs are roaming freely
across our lands.

252
00:25:20,768 --> 00:25:24,439
Unchecked. Unchallenged.
Killing at will.

253
00:25:25,064 --> 00:25:27,942
Orcs bearing the White Hand of Saruman.

254
00:25:35,783 --> 00:25:41,581
Why do you lay these troubles
on an already troubled mind?

255
00:25:41,748 --> 00:25:44,208
Can you not see?

256
00:25:44,375 --> 00:25:49,422
Your uncle is wearied
by your malcontent...

257
00:25:49,589 --> 00:25:52,133
...your warmongering.

258
00:25:54,343 --> 00:25:56,304
Warmongering?

259
00:25:56,471 --> 00:25:58,639
How long is it since
Saruman bought you?

260
00:25:59,474 --> 00:26:01,851
What was the promised price, Grima?

261
00:26:02,101 --> 00:26:05,772
When all the Men are dead,
you will take your share of the treasure?

262
00:26:18,201 --> 00:26:20,870
Too long have you watched my sister.

263
00:26:21,037 --> 00:26:23,039
Too long have you haunted her steps.

264
00:26:31,089 --> 00:26:35,426
You see much, Eomer, son of Eomund.

265
00:26:35,593 --> 00:26:36,761
Too much.

266
00:26:37,261 --> 00:26:38,930
[GRUNTING]

267
00:26:39,097 --> 00:26:43,893
You are banished forthwith
from the kingdom of Rohan...

268
00:26:44,060 --> 00:26:48,856
...and all its domains
under pain of death.

269
00:26:49,315 --> 00:26:51,651
You have no authority here.

270
00:26:51,818 --> 00:26:54,278
Your orders mean nothing.

271
00:26:54,821 --> 00:26:58,658
This order does not come from me.

272
00:26:58,825 --> 00:27:01,035
It comes from the king.

273
00:27:01,577 --> 00:27:04,247
He signed it this morning.

274
00:27:07,166 --> 00:27:08,835
[YELLS]

275
00:27:35,778 --> 00:27:38,489
Keep breathing. That's the key.

276
00:27:38,698 --> 00:27:40,408
Breathe.

277
00:27:44,579 --> 00:27:48,374
They've run as if the very whips
of their masters were behind them.

278
00:28:04,599 --> 00:28:06,559
ORC 1:
We're not going no further...

279
00:28:06,726 --> 00:28:08,728
...until we've had a breather.

280
00:28:09,270 --> 00:28:11,230
Get a fire going!

281
00:28:15,318 --> 00:28:16,903
Merry!

282
00:28:17,236 --> 00:28:18,613
Merry!

283
00:28:20,281 --> 00:28:25,494
I think we might have made a mistake
leaving the Shire, Pippin.

284
00:28:30,791 --> 00:28:33,836
[GROANING]

285
00:28:34,921 --> 00:28:37,131
What's making that noise?

286
00:28:38,716 --> 00:28:40,176
It's the trees.

287
00:28:40,927 --> 00:28:41,969
What?

288
00:28:42,303 --> 00:28:46,140
You remember the Old Forest,
on the borders of Buckland?

289
00:28:46,307 --> 00:28:50,811
Folk used to say there was something in
the water that made the trees grow tall...

290
00:28:50,978 --> 00:28:52,521
...and come alive.

291
00:28:52,772 --> 00:28:54,440
Alive?

292
00:28:55,316 --> 00:28:57,026
Trees that could whisper...

293
00:28:58,027 --> 00:29:00,488
...talk to each other...

294
00:29:00,655 --> 00:29:02,531
...even move.

295
00:29:04,158 --> 00:29:06,369
I'm starving.

296
00:29:06,535 --> 00:29:10,665
We ain't had nothing but maggoty bread
for three stinking days.

297
00:29:10,957 --> 00:29:12,250
Yeah!

298
00:29:12,458 --> 00:29:15,711
Why can't we have some meat?!

299
00:29:18,089 --> 00:29:20,299
What about them?

300
00:29:20,466 --> 00:29:22,343
They're fresh.

301
00:29:23,010 --> 00:29:26,806
They are not for eating.

302
00:29:32,770 --> 00:29:34,730
What about their legs?

303
00:29:34,897 --> 00:29:37,233
They don't need those.

304
00:29:38,693 --> 00:29:41,862
-They look tasty.
LEADER: Get back, scum!

305
00:29:43,698 --> 00:29:48,577
The prisoners go to Saruman.
Alive and unspoiled.

306
00:29:48,953 --> 00:29:50,871
Alive?

307
00:29:53,833 --> 00:29:58,129
Why alive?
Do they give good sport?

308
00:30:00,506 --> 00:30:03,884
They have something.
An Elvish weapon.

309
00:30:04,051 --> 00:30:07,096
The master wants it for the war.

310
00:30:09,974 --> 00:30:11,851
-They think we have the Ring.
-Shh.

311
00:30:12,018 --> 00:30:14,437
As soon as they find out we don't,
we're dead.

312
00:30:16,314 --> 00:30:18,274
Just a mouthful...

313
00:30:18,441 --> 00:30:19,650
...a bit of the flank.

314
00:30:26,449 --> 00:30:30,036
Looks like meat's back on the menu,
boys.

315
00:30:30,244 --> 00:30:32,163
[ROARING]

316
00:30:36,625 --> 00:30:37,877
Pippin.

317
00:30:38,044 --> 00:30:39,754
Let's go.

318
00:30:48,179 --> 00:30:49,722
Go on.

319
00:30:49,889 --> 00:30:51,390
Call for help.

320
00:30:52,767 --> 00:30:53,851
squeal

321
00:30:54,060 --> 00:30:57,271
No one's going to save you now.

322
00:31:01,275 --> 00:31:02,818
[HORSES NEIGHING]

323
00:31:06,447 --> 00:31:07,865
MERRY:
Pippin!

324
00:31:32,098 --> 00:31:34,600
A red sun rises.

325
00:31:35,101 --> 00:31:38,020
Blood has been spilled this night.

326
00:31:50,491 --> 00:31:52,952
[HOOVES BEATING]

327
00:32:09,260 --> 00:32:11,137
Riders of Rohan...

328
00:32:11,554 --> 00:32:13,973
...what news from the Mark?

329
00:32:41,709 --> 00:32:46,130
What business does an Elf, a Man
and a Dwarf have in the Riddermark?

330
00:32:46,922 --> 00:32:48,174
Speak quickly!

331
00:32:48,507 --> 00:32:53,179
Give me your name, horse-master,
and I shall give you mine.

332
00:33:02,313 --> 00:33:04,899
I would cut off your head, Dwarf...

333
00:33:05,399 --> 00:33:07,693
...if it stood but a little higher
from the ground.

334
00:33:08,736 --> 00:33:10,821
You would die before your stroke fell.

335
00:33:19,538 --> 00:33:21,415
I am Aragorn, son of Arathorn.

336
00:33:21,749 --> 00:33:25,961
This is Gimli, son of Gléin,
and Legolas of the Woodland Realm.

337
00:33:26,128 --> 00:33:29,423
We are friends of Rohan
and of Théoden, your king.

338
00:33:31,050 --> 00:33:34,845
Théoden no longer recognizes
friend from foe.

339
00:33:35,054 --> 00:33:37,264
Not even his own kin.

340
00:33:41,769 --> 00:33:43,729
Saruman has poisoned the mind
of the king...

341
00:33:43,938 --> 00:33:45,856
...and claimed lordship over these lands.

342
00:33:47,816 --> 00:33:50,819
My company are those loyal to Rohan.

343
00:33:50,986 --> 00:33:52,738
And for that, we are banished.

344
00:33:54,823 --> 00:33:58,118
The White Wizard is cunning.

345
00:33:58,786 --> 00:34:01,205
He walks here and there, they say...

346
00:34:01,372 --> 00:34:03,457
...as an old man hooded and cloaked.

347
00:34:05,292 --> 00:34:09,088
And everywhere, his spies
slip past our nets.

348
00:34:09,255 --> 00:34:11,465
We are no spies.

349
00:34:11,632 --> 00:34:14,593
We track a party of Uruk-hai
westward across the plain.

350
00:34:14,885 --> 00:34:17,221
They have taken two of our friends
captive.

351
00:34:18,013 --> 00:34:20,474
The Uruks are destroyed.
We slaughtered them during the night.

352
00:34:20,641 --> 00:34:23,811
But there were two Hobbits.
Did you see two Hobbits with them?

353
00:34:23,978 --> 00:34:26,981
They would be small.
Only children to your eyes.

354
00:34:30,276 --> 00:34:32,278
We left none alive.

355
00:34:32,987 --> 00:34:35,864
We piled the carcasses and burned them.

356
00:34:41,328 --> 00:34:42,580
Dead?

357
00:34:45,583 --> 00:34:47,293
I am sorry.

358
00:34:51,630 --> 00:34:52,673
[WHISTLES]

359
00:34:52,840 --> 00:34:55,134
Hasufel! Arod!

360
00:34:57,011 --> 00:35:01,640
May these horses bear you to better
fortune than their former masters.

361
00:35:02,891 --> 00:35:04,518
Farewell.

362
00:35:09,648 --> 00:35:11,942
Look for your friends.

363
00:35:12,359 --> 00:35:14,612
But do not trust to hope.

364
00:35:16,322 --> 00:35:18,866
It has forsaken these lands.

365
00:35:19,074 --> 00:35:21,076
We ride north!

366
00:36:11,710 --> 00:36:13,587
It's one of their wee belts.

367
00:36:14,588 --> 00:36:17,007
[SPEAKS IN ELVISH]

368
00:36:21,720 --> 00:36:23,514
[YELLS]

369
00:36:27,309 --> 00:36:29,353
We failed them.

370
00:36:43,409 --> 00:36:45,619
A Hobbit lay here.

371
00:36:47,454 --> 00:36:49,123
And the other.

372
00:36:59,883 --> 00:37:01,468
They crawled.

373
00:37:05,639 --> 00:37:07,766
Their hands were bound.

374
00:37:19,903 --> 00:37:21,739
Their bonds were cut.

375
00:37:37,171 --> 00:37:39,298
They ran over here.

376
00:37:42,968 --> 00:37:44,178
They were followed.

377
00:37:47,347 --> 00:37:49,099
MERRY:
The belt!

378
00:37:52,978 --> 00:37:54,188
Run!

379
00:37:57,816 --> 00:37:59,193
Tracks lead away from the battle...

380
00:38:04,031 --> 00:38:06,200
...into Fangorn Forest.

381
00:38:07,034 --> 00:38:08,494
Fangorn?

382
00:38:08,702 --> 00:38:11,288
What madness drove them in there?

383
00:38:27,554 --> 00:38:28,847
[TREES GROANING]

384
00:38:29,014 --> 00:38:32,017
PIPPIN:
Did we lose him? I think we lost him.

385
00:38:32,351 --> 00:38:35,062
[SNARLING]

386
00:38:38,732 --> 00:38:42,152
I'm going to rip out
your filthy little innards!

387
00:38:48,325 --> 00:38:49,368
Come here!

388
00:38:54,873 --> 00:38:57,459
Trees. Climb a tree.

389
00:39:06,802 --> 00:39:08,554
He's gone.

390
00:39:09,179 --> 00:39:10,389
[GROWLING]

391
00:39:20,607 --> 00:39:22,943
Merry!

392
00:39:24,361 --> 00:39:27,364
[GROANS]

393
00:39:34,413 --> 00:39:38,792
Let's put a maggot hole in your belly!

394
00:39:45,924 --> 00:39:47,467
Run, Merry!

395
00:39:53,807 --> 00:39:55,601
[HOBBITS GRUNTING]

396
00:39:57,311 --> 00:40:01,607
Little Orcs.

397
00:40:01,815 --> 00:40:04,109
It's talking, Merry.
The tree is talking.

398
00:40:04,318 --> 00:40:06,153
Tree?

399
00:40:06,320 --> 00:40:09,323
I am no tree!

400
00:40:09,531 --> 00:40:11,742
I am an Ent.

401
00:40:12,326 --> 00:40:14,453
A tree-herder.

402
00:40:14,953 --> 00:40:16,955
A shepherd of the forest.

403
00:40:17,122 --> 00:40:18,457
Don't talk to it, Merry.

404
00:40:18,957 --> 00:40:20,459
Don't encourage it!

405
00:40:20,626 --> 00:40:24,880
Treebeard, some call me.

406
00:40:25,047 --> 00:40:27,007
And whose side are you on?

407
00:40:27,633 --> 00:40:29,259
Side?

408
00:40:29,468 --> 00:40:32,346
I am on nobody's side...

409
00:40:32,679 --> 00:40:38,018
...because nobody's on my side,
little Orc.

410
00:40:38,852 --> 00:40:43,482
Nobody cares for the woods anymore.

411
00:40:43,857 --> 00:40:46,234
We're not Orcs! We're Hobbits!

412
00:40:46,401 --> 00:40:48,695
Hobbits?

413
00:40:49,947 --> 00:40:54,868
Never heard of a Hobbit before.

414
00:40:55,994 --> 00:40:59,289
Sounds like Orc mischief to me!

415
00:40:59,456 --> 00:41:00,499
[HOBBITS GROANING]

416
00:41:00,666 --> 00:41:02,876
They come with fire.

417
00:41:03,085 --> 00:41:05,671
They come with axes.

418
00:41:05,879 --> 00:41:10,676
Gnawing, biting, breaking,
hacking, burning!

419
00:41:10,884 --> 00:41:14,680
Destroyers and usurpers! Curse them!
-No!

420
00:41:14,888 --> 00:41:17,683
You don't understand. We're Hobbits!

421
00:41:17,891 --> 00:41:19,685
Half lings!

422
00:41:19,893 --> 00:41:21,019
Shire-folk!

423
00:41:21,186 --> 00:41:23,522
Maybe you are...

424
00:41:23,814 --> 00:41:27,442
...and maybe you aren't.

425
00:41:28,527 --> 00:41:32,447
The White Wizard will know.

426
00:41:33,240 --> 00:41:35,200
The White Wizard?

427
00:41:36,702 --> 00:41:38,203
Saruman.

428
00:41:50,757 --> 00:41:52,467
GOLLUM:
See? See?

429
00:41:52,676 --> 00:41:55,053
We've led you out.

430
00:41:55,220 --> 00:41:57,764
Hurry, Hobbitses. Hurry!

431
00:42:00,851 --> 00:42:03,437
Very lucky we find you.

432
00:42:10,068 --> 00:42:11,778
Nice Hobbit.

433
00:42:13,447 --> 00:42:17,951
Oh! It's a bog. He's led us into a swamp.

434
00:42:18,118 --> 00:42:20,746
A swamp, yes, yes.

435
00:42:21,496 --> 00:42:26,251
Come, master. We will take you
on safe paths through the mist.

436
00:42:28,545 --> 00:42:32,007
Come, Hobbits! Come! We go quickly.

437
00:42:35,260 --> 00:42:37,888
I found it. I did.

438
00:42:38,096 --> 00:42:40,766
The way through the marshes.

439
00:42:40,974 --> 00:42:44,478
Orcs don't use it.
Orcs don't know it.

440
00:42:44,644 --> 00:42:48,732
They go around for miles and miles.

441
00:42:48,982 --> 00:42:50,358
Come quickly.

442
00:42:50,567 --> 00:42:54,613
Soft and quick as shadows we must be.

443
00:42:55,781 --> 00:42:59,117
I hate this place. It's too quiet.

444
00:42:59,284 --> 00:43:01,536
There's been no sight nor sound
of a bird for two days.

445
00:43:01,703 --> 00:43:05,123
No, no birdses to eat.

446
00:43:05,373 --> 00:43:09,628
No crunchable birdses.

447
00:43:10,212 --> 00:43:13,090
And we are famished! Yes!

448
00:43:13,256 --> 00:43:17,552
Famished we are, precious!

449
00:43:32,526 --> 00:43:34,027
Here.

450
00:43:35,195 --> 00:43:37,239
GOLLUM:
What does it eats?

451
00:43:37,405 --> 00:43:39,366
Is it tasty?

452
00:43:41,868 --> 00:43:43,745
[COUGHS]

453
00:43:44,663 --> 00:43:47,290
It tries to chokes us!

454
00:43:47,541 --> 00:43:51,211
We can't eats Hobbit food!

455
00:43:52,921 --> 00:43:56,967
We must starve!

456
00:43:57,134 --> 00:43:59,553
Well, starve, then. And good riddance!

457
00:44:00,262 --> 00:44:02,514
Oh, cruel Hobbit.

458
00:44:02,681 --> 00:44:05,559
It does not care if we be hungry.

459
00:44:05,767 --> 00:44:10,564
Does not care if we should die.

460
00:44:11,148 --> 00:44:13,984
Not like master.

461
00:44:15,360 --> 00:44:17,445
Master cares.

462
00:44:18,613 --> 00:44:20,490
Master knows.

463
00:44:22,951 --> 00:44:24,911
Yes.

464
00:44:25,078 --> 00:44:27,706
Precious.

465
00:44:31,293 --> 00:44:34,921
Once it takes hold of us...

466
00:44:36,756 --> 00:44:40,969
...it never lets go.

467
00:44:41,636 --> 00:44:42,804
Don't touch me!

468
00:45:15,295 --> 00:45:17,172
SAM:
There are dead things!

469
00:45:17,339 --> 00:45:19,132
Dead faces in the water.

470
00:45:23,929 --> 00:45:27,933
GOLLUM:
All dead. All rotten.

471
00:45:28,433 --> 00:45:32,229
Elves and Men and Orcses.

472
00:45:32,395 --> 00:45:36,024
A great battle long ago.

473
00:45:36,816 --> 00:45:38,568
Dead Marshes.

474
00:45:38,777 --> 00:45:41,488
Yes. Yes, that is their name.

475
00:45:43,156 --> 00:45:44,950
This way.

476
00:45:45,158 --> 00:45:47,869
Don't follow the lights.

477
00:45:49,663 --> 00:45:53,458
Careful now! Or Hobbits go down
to join the dead ones...

478
00:45:53,667 --> 00:45:57,796
...and light little candles
of their own.

479
00:46:23,989 --> 00:46:25,490
Frodo!

480
00:47:02,652 --> 00:47:05,322
[FRODO GASPS]

481
00:47:09,993 --> 00:47:14,664
-Go||um?
-Don't follow the lights.

482
00:47:14,831 --> 00:47:16,624
FRODO: GOLLUM!
-Mr. Frodo!

483
00:47:16,875 --> 00:47:18,752
Are you all right?

484
00:47:22,130 --> 00:47:24,799
[THUNDER ROLLING]

485
00:47:47,572 --> 00:47:50,575
GOLLUM:
80 bright.

486
00:47:50,784 --> 00:47:54,579
So beautiful.

487
00:47:54,788 --> 00:47:58,583
Our precious.

488
00:48:00,043 --> 00:48:01,503
What did you say?

489
00:48:01,795 --> 00:48:03,963
Master should be resting.

490
00:48:04,130 --> 00:48:08,218
Master needs to keep up his strength.

491
00:48:10,178 --> 00:48:13,431
-Who are you?
-Mustn't ask us. Not its business.

492
00:48:13,598 --> 00:48:15,100
GOLLUM. GOLLUM.

493
00:48:15,266 --> 00:48:17,143
Gandalf told me you were
one of the river-folk.

494
00:48:17,310 --> 00:48:21,356
<i>Cold be heart and hand and bone
Cold be travelers far from home</i>

495
00:48:21,523 --> 00:48:23,108
He said your life was a sad story.

496
00:48:23,316 --> 00:48:27,821
<i>They do not see what lies ahead
When sun has failed and moon is dead</i>

497
00:48:27,987 --> 00:48:30,990
You were not so very different
from a Hobbit once.

498
00:48:31,157 --> 00:48:32,951
Were you?

499
00:48:35,120 --> 00:48:37,372
Sméagol.

500
00:48:42,085 --> 00:48:44,629
What did you call me?

501
00:48:45,964 --> 00:48:48,716
That was your name once, wasn't it?

502
00:48:49,342 --> 00:48:51,636
Along time ago.

503
00:48:52,470 --> 00:48:54,639
My name.

504
00:48:55,723 --> 00:48:57,225
My name.

505
00:49:04,149 --> 00:49:06,651
Sméagol.

506
00:49:07,277 --> 00:49:09,154
[RINGWRAITH SCREECHING]

507
00:49:10,738 --> 00:49:12,365
Black Riders!

508
00:49:12,532 --> 00:49:13,867
Hide! Hide!

509
00:49:14,033 --> 00:49:16,411
[FRODO GROANING]

510
00:49:24,461 --> 00:49:26,754
Come on, Frodo. Come on!

511
00:49:26,921 --> 00:49:30,550
SMEAGOL: Quick! They will see us!
They will see us!

512
00:49:31,384 --> 00:49:34,012
-I thought they were dead.
-Dead?

513
00:49:34,179 --> 00:49:37,098
No, you cannot kill them. No.

514
00:49:53,406 --> 00:49:55,575
[ROARS]

515
00:50:04,250 --> 00:50:05,376
SMEAGOL:
Wraiths!

516
00:50:05,543 --> 00:50:07,754
Wraiths on wings!

517
00:50:10,673 --> 00:50:13,301
[SCREECHING]

518
00:50:15,720 --> 00:50:17,805
They are calling for it.

519
00:50:18,014 --> 00:50:21,476
They are calling for the precious.

520
00:50:23,686 --> 00:50:25,813
Mr. Frodo! It's all right.

521
00:50:25,980 --> 00:50:27,232
I'm here.

522
00:50:34,948 --> 00:50:37,116
[ROARS]

523
00:50:43,248 --> 00:50:44,791
SMEAGOL:
Hurry, Hobbits.

524
00:50:45,333 --> 00:50:49,254
The Black Gate is very close.

525
00:50:54,968 --> 00:50:55,969
[SPITS]

526
00:50:56,135 --> 00:50:58,012
Orc blood.

527
00:51:08,022 --> 00:51:09,774
These are strange tracks.

528
00:51:11,067 --> 00:51:13,027
The air is so close in here.

529
00:51:14,237 --> 00:51:16,656
This forest is old.

530
00:51:17,490 --> 00:51:19,492
Very old.

531
00:51:21,202 --> 00:51:23,496
Full of memory...

532
00:51:26,124 --> 00:51:28,501
...and anger.

533
00:51:29,043 --> 00:51:32,130
[TREES GROANING]

534
00:51:34,632 --> 00:51:37,510
The trees are speaking to each other.

535
00:51:37,677 --> 00:51:39,178
ARAGORN:
Gimli!

536
00:51:39,345 --> 00:51:41,306
Lower your ax.

537
00:51:44,100 --> 00:51:46,853
They have feelings, my friend.

538
00:51:47,395 --> 00:51:49,397
The Elves began it.

539
00:51:49,564 --> 00:51:54,319
Waking up the trees,
teaching them to speak.

540
00:51:54,819 --> 00:51:57,155
Talking trees.

541
00:51:57,822 --> 00:52:00,825
What do trees have to talk about?

542
00:52:01,034 --> 00:52:04,245
Except the consistency
of squirrel droppings.

543
00:52:07,832 --> 00:52:09,292
[IN ELVISH]
Something’s out there.

544
00:52:15,840 --> 00:52:17,634
[IN ELVISH]
What do you see?

545
00:52:18,176 --> 00:52:20,637
[IN ENGLISH]
The White Wizard approaches.

546
00:52:26,809 --> 00:52:31,105
[IN ENGLISH] Do not let him speak.
He will put a spell on us.

547
00:52:40,698 --> 00:52:42,950
We must be quick.

548
00:52:58,508 --> 00:53:02,178
WHITE WIZARD: You are tracking
the footsteps of two young Hobbits.

549
00:53:02,762 --> 00:53:04,180
Where are they?

550
00:53:04,347 --> 00:53:07,892
WHITE WIZARD: They passed this way
the day before yesterday.

551
00:53:08,101 --> 00:53:12,355
They met someone they did not expect.

552
00:53:12,522 --> 00:53:14,649
Does that comfort you?

553
00:53:14,816 --> 00:53:16,776
Who are you?

554
00:53:18,236 --> 00:53:20,238
Show yourself!

555
00:53:29,122 --> 00:53:31,124
It cannot be.

556
00:53:34,043 --> 00:53:35,128
Forgive me.

557
00:53:36,713 --> 00:53:38,631
I mistook you for Saruman.

558
00:53:39,424 --> 00:53:42,176
I am Saruman.

559
00:53:43,720 --> 00:53:47,640
Or rather, Saruman
as he should have been.

560
00:53:48,558 --> 00:53:50,059
You fell.

561
00:53:51,519 --> 00:53:54,063
Through fire...

562
00:53:54,230 --> 00:53:55,523
...and water.

563
00:53:56,983 --> 00:53:59,527
<i>From the lowest dungeon
to the highest peak...</i>

564
00:53:59,694 --> 00:54:03,448
<i>...I fought with the Balrog
Of Morgoth.</i>

565
00:54:04,198 --> 00:54:06,576
[ROARING AND YELLING]

566
00:54:19,297 --> 00:54:22,008
GANDALF: <i>Until at last
I threw down my enemy...</i>

567
00:54:22,175 --> 00:54:26,679
<i>...and smote his ruin
upon the mountainside.</i>

568
00:54:32,685 --> 00:54:35,229
<i>Darkness took me...</i>

569
00:54:35,980 --> 00:54:40,067
<i>...and I strayed out of thought
and time.</i>

570
00:54:40,818 --> 00:54:43,905
<i>Stars wheeled overhead...</i>

571
00:54:44,197 --> 00:54:48,701
<i>...and every day was as long
as a life age of the Earth.</i>

572
00:54:50,787 --> 00:54:52,914
<i>But it was not the end.</i>

573
00:54:53,206 --> 00:54:56,000
<i>I felt life in me again.</i>

574
00:54:57,919 --> 00:55:00,463
<i>I've been sent back...</i>

575
00:55:00,630 --> 00:55:02,215
...until my task is done.

576
00:55:02,632 --> 00:55:04,509
Gandalf.

577
00:55:05,218 --> 00:55:07,220
Gandalf?

578
00:55:07,595 --> 00:55:09,388
Yes.

579
00:55:12,225 --> 00:55:13,976
That was what they used to call me.

580
00:55:16,854 --> 00:55:19,106
Gandalf the Grey.

581
00:55:20,441 --> 00:55:22,235
That was my name.

582
00:55:22,443 --> 00:55:23,820
Gandalf.

583
00:55:25,780 --> 00:55:27,865
I am Gandalf the White.

584
00:55:30,868 --> 00:55:33,955
And I come back to you now...

585
00:55:34,121 --> 00:55:36,624
...at the turn of the tide.

586
00:55:37,750 --> 00:55:40,753
One stage of your journey is over.
Another begins.

587
00:55:41,462 --> 00:55:44,632
-We must travel to Edoras with all speed.
GIMLI: Edoras?

588
00:55:45,550 --> 00:55:47,593
That is no short distance!

589
00:55:47,844 --> 00:55:51,055
We hear of trouble in Rohan.
It goes "I with the king.

590
00:55:51,264 --> 00:55:53,349
Yes, and it will not be easily cured.

591
00:55:53,516 --> 00:55:56,936
Then we have run all this way for nothing?

592
00:55:57,103 --> 00:55:59,105
Are we to leave those poor Hobbits here...

593
00:55:59,272 --> 00:56:03,192
...in this horrid, dark, dank,
tree-infested--?

594
00:56:03,359 --> 00:56:05,695
[TREES GROANING]

595
00:56:06,112 --> 00:56:09,282
I mean, charming...

596
00:56:09,448 --> 00:56:12,201
...quite charming forest.

597
00:56:12,785 --> 00:56:16,414
It was more than mere chance that
brought Merry and Pippin to Fangorn.

598
00:56:16,581 --> 00:56:20,918
A great power has been sleeping here
for many long years.

599
00:56:21,085 --> 00:56:24,547
The coming of Merry and Pippin
will be like the falling of small stones...

600
00:56:24,714 --> 00:56:28,050
...that starts an avalanche
in the mountains.

601
00:56:28,217 --> 00:56:30,386
In one thing you have not changed,
dear friend.

602
00:56:30,553 --> 00:56:34,974
-Hm?
-You still speak in riddles.

603
00:56:37,810 --> 00:56:44,233
A thing is about to happen that has not
happened since the Elder Days.

604
00:56:44,400 --> 00:56:48,029
The Ents are going to wake up...

605
00:56:48,571 --> 00:56:53,075
-...and find that they are strong.
-Strong?!

606
00:56:53,826 --> 00:56:54,994
Oh, that's good.

607
00:56:55,161 --> 00:56:57,872
So stop your fretting, Master Dwarf.

608
00:56:58,956 --> 00:57:01,208
Merry and Pippin are quite safe.

609
00:57:01,375 --> 00:57:05,046
In fact, they are far safer
than you are about to be.

610
00:57:05,212 --> 00:57:08,966
This new Gandalf‘s more grumpy
than the old one.

611
00:57:09,216 --> 00:57:11,260
[WHISTLING]

612
00:57:20,645 --> 00:57:22,480
[HORSE NEIGHS]

613
00:57:31,197 --> 00:57:32,657
That is one of the Mearas...

614
00:57:32,865 --> 00:57:35,618
...unless my eyes are cheated
by some spell.

615
00:57:53,219 --> 00:57:55,513
GAN DALF:
Shadowfax.

616
00:57:58,099 --> 00:58:00,685
He is the lord of all horses...

617
00:58:02,311 --> 00:58:06,232
...and has been my friend
through many dangers.

618
00:58:20,496 --> 00:58:24,083
TREEBEARD:
<i>O rowan mine</i>

619
00:58:24,250 --> 00:58:28,045
<i>I saw you shine</i>

620
00:58:28,212 --> 00:58:31,757
<i>Upon a summer's day</i>

621
00:58:32,842 --> 00:58:37,346
<i>Upon your head
How golden-red</i>

622
00:58:37,513 --> 00:58:42,226
<i>The crown you bore aloft</i>

623
00:58:42,435 --> 00:58:44,812
Such a beautiful verse.

624
00:58:44,979 --> 00:58:49,900
-Is it much further?
-Bru-ra-hroom. Don't be hasty.

625
00:58:50,067 --> 00:58:53,320
You might call it far, perhaps.

626
00:58:54,238 --> 00:58:58,034
My home lies deep in the forest...

627
00:58:58,242 --> 00:59:02,121
...near the roots of the mountain.

628
00:59:03,456 --> 00:59:07,126
I told Gandalf I would keep you safe.

629
00:59:07,334 --> 00:59:11,338
And safe is where I'll keep you.

630
00:59:11,589 --> 00:59:15,968
I believe you will enjoy this next one too.

631
00:59:16,343 --> 00:59:19,346
It's one of my own compositions.

632
00:59:19,513 --> 00:59:20,723
Right.

633
00:59:20,890 --> 00:59:27,021
<i>Beneath the roof of sleeping leaves</i>

634
00:59:27,188 --> 00:59:32,068
<i>And the dreams of trees unfold</i>

635
00:59:32,234 --> 00:59:38,699
<i>When woodland halls are green and cool</i>

636
00:59:38,866 --> 00:59:42,995
<i>And the wind is in the West</i>

637
00:59:43,412 --> 00:59:46,082
<i>Come back to me</i>

638
00:59:46,624 --> 00:59:51,087
<i>Come back to me</i>

639
00:59:51,253 --> 00:59:57,676
<i>And say my land is best</i>

640
00:59:59,178 --> 01:00:01,138
Oh.

641
01:00:05,142 --> 01:00:08,813
Sleep, little Shirelings.

642
01:00:09,021 --> 01:00:12,566
Heed no nightly noise.

643
01:00:12,733 --> 01:00:16,654
Sleep tiII morning light.

644
01:00:18,280 --> 01:00:22,451
I have business in the forest.

645
01:00:22,618 --> 01:00:28,165
There are many to call.
Many that must come.

646
01:00:29,375 --> 01:00:34,046
The Shadow lies on Fangorn.

647
01:00:34,213 --> 01:00:39,927
The withering of all woods
is drawing near.

648
01:00:49,478 --> 01:00:53,732
The veiling shadow that glowers
in the east takes shape.

649
01:00:54,567 --> 01:00:57,153
Sauron will suffer no rival.

650
01:00:57,570 --> 01:01:01,866
From the summit of Barad-dﬂr,
his Eye watches ceaselessly.

651
01:01:02,074 --> 01:01:05,452
But he is not so mighty yet
that he is above fear.

652
01:01:06,495 --> 01:01:08,455
Doubt ever gnaws at him.

653
01:01:08,622 --> 01:01:11,208
The rumor has reached him.

654
01:01:11,375 --> 01:01:14,336
The heir of Numenor still lives.

655
01:01:15,296 --> 01:01:18,132
Sauron fears you, Aragorn.

656
01:01:19,425 --> 01:01:21,635
He fears what you may become.

657
01:01:22,887 --> 01:01:26,307
And so he'll strike hard and fast
at the world of Men.

658
01:01:26,473 --> 01:01:30,102
He will use his puppet, Saruman,
to destroy Rohan.

659
01:01:30,269 --> 01:01:31,770
War is coming.

660
01:01:31,937 --> 01:01:35,524
Rohan must defend itself,
and therein lies our first challenge...

661
01:01:35,691 --> 01:01:38,110
...for Rohan is weak and ready to fall.

662
01:01:38,277 --> 01:01:41,989
The king's mind is enslaved,
it's an old device of Saruman's.

663
01:01:42,156 --> 01:01:45,242
His hold over King Théoden
is now very strong.

664
01:01:45,409 --> 01:01:50,122
Sauron and Saruman
are tightening the noose.

665
01:01:50,915 --> 01:01:53,083
But for all their cunning...

666
01:01:53,250 --> 01:01:55,836
...we have one advantage.

667
01:01:57,963 --> 01:02:00,549
The Ring remains hidden.

668
01:02:01,634 --> 01:02:03,552
And that we should seek to destroy it...

669
01:02:03,719 --> 01:02:06,680
...has not yet entered
their darkest dreams.

670
01:02:07,264 --> 01:02:10,601
And so the weapon of the enemy
is moving towards Mordor...

671
01:02:10,768 --> 01:02:12,269
...in the hands of a Hobbit.

672
01:02:12,436 --> 01:02:16,523
Each day brings it closer
to the fires of Mount Doom.

673
01:02:16,690 --> 01:02:19,318
We must trust now in Frodo.

674
01:02:19,485 --> 01:02:21,320
Everything depends upon speed...

675
01:02:21,487 --> 01:02:24,490
...and the secrecy of his quest.

676
01:02:26,450 --> 01:02:29,787
Do not regret your decision to leave him.

677
01:02:30,663 --> 01:02:33,415
Frodo must finish this task alone.

678
01:02:34,166 --> 01:02:36,460
He's not alone.

679
01:02:36,669 --> 01:02:38,337
Sam went with him.

680
01:02:39,004 --> 01:02:40,214
Did he?

681
01:02:40,381 --> 01:02:45,010
Did he, indeed? Good.

682
01:02:45,678 --> 01:02:48,055
Yes, very good.

683
01:02:56,063 --> 01:03:00,943
SMEAGOL:
The Black Gate of Mordor.

684
01:03:03,737 --> 01:03:06,240
Oh, save us.

685
01:03:11,996 --> 01:03:15,249
My old Gaffer would have a thing or two
to say if he could see us now.

686
01:03:17,501 --> 01:03:21,964
SMEAGOL: Master says to
show him the way into Mordor.

687
01:03:22,131 --> 01:03:25,551
So good Sméagol does,
master says so.

688
01:03:25,718 --> 01:03:26,969
I did.

689
01:03:35,728 --> 01:03:37,730
That's it, then.

690
01:03:39,273 --> 01:03:40,566
We can't get past that.

691
01:03:41,108 --> 01:03:44,028
[EASTERLINGS YELLING
INDISTINCTLY]

692
01:03:51,744 --> 01:03:54,330
[HORNS BLOWING]

693
01:04:04,381 --> 01:04:06,425
[ROARS]

694
01:04:25,778 --> 01:04:27,112
Look!

695
01:04:27,279 --> 01:04:28,739
The gate.

696
01:04:28,906 --> 01:04:30,115
It's opening!

697
01:04:37,539 --> 01:04:39,541
I can see a way down.

698
01:04:40,292 --> 01:04:42,378
Sam, no!

699
01:04:44,546 --> 01:04:45,923
Master!

700
01:06:02,499 --> 01:06:05,210
[EASTERLINGS YELLING
INDISTINCTLY]

701
01:06:09,756 --> 01:06:13,302
-I do not ask you to come with me, <i>Sam.</i>
-I know, Mr. Frodo.

702
01:06:14,052 --> 01:06:17,222
I doubt even these Elvish cloaks
will hide us in there.

703
01:06:17,639 --> 01:06:19,516
-Now!
SMEAGOL: No!

704
01:06:20,058 --> 01:06:22,060
No! No, master!

705
01:06:22,227 --> 01:06:25,230
They catch you! They catch you!

706
01:06:26,523 --> 01:06:29,067
Don't take it to him.

707
01:06:32,029 --> 01:06:34,740
He wants the precious.

708
01:06:34,907 --> 01:06:37,951
Always he is looking for it.

709
01:06:38,118 --> 01:06:42,039
And the precious is wanting
to go back to him.

710
01:06:42,247 --> 01:06:46,168
But we mustn't let him have it.

711
01:06:52,549 --> 01:06:54,676
No! There's another way.

712
01:06:54,843 --> 01:06:57,513
More secret. A dark way.

713
01:06:57,804 --> 01:07:01,475
-Why haven't you spoken of this before?
-Because master did not ask.

714
01:07:01,934 --> 01:07:03,060
He's up to something.

715
01:07:03,644 --> 01:07:06,230
Are you saying there's another way
into Mordor?

716
01:07:06,438 --> 01:07:09,149
Yes. There's a path...

717
01:07:09,316 --> 01:07:11,818
...and some stairs.

718
01:07:12,027 --> 01:07:13,695
And then...

719
01:07:13,862 --> 01:07:17,199
...a tunnel.

720
01:07:17,574 --> 01:07:19,785
[RUMBLING]

721
01:07:31,171 --> 01:07:32,965
He's led us this far, <i>Sam.</i>

722
01:07:33,131 --> 01:07:34,550
Mr. Frodo, no.

723
01:07:35,676 --> 01:07:37,135
He's been true to his word.

724
01:07:42,015 --> 01:07:43,225
No.

725
01:07:45,352 --> 01:07:46,979
Lead the way, Sméagol.

726
01:07:47,604 --> 01:07:51,525
Good Sméagol always helps.

727
01:08:25,517 --> 01:08:26,518
Hello?

728
01:08:28,937 --> 01:08:31,023
Treebeard?

729
01:08:31,648 --> 01:08:33,025
Where has he gone?

730
01:08:33,191 --> 01:08:35,652
PIPPIN:
I had the loveliest dream last night.

731
01:08:36,278 --> 01:08:38,989
There was this large barrel,
full of pipe-weed.

732
01:08:39,156 --> 01:08:41,658
And we smoked all of it.
And then...

733
01:08:42,159 --> 01:08:44,077
...you were sick.

734
01:08:45,662 --> 01:08:48,540
I'd give anything for a whiff of Old Toby.

735
01:08:49,625 --> 01:08:51,710
[GROANING]

736
01:08:52,044 --> 01:08:53,962
Did you hear that?

737
01:09:01,053 --> 01:09:02,554
There it is again.

738
01:09:03,388 --> 01:09:06,975
Something's not right here.
Not right at all.

739
01:09:07,142 --> 01:09:09,269
[ENTISH GROAN]

740
01:09:11,813 --> 01:09:14,733
You just said something...Treeish.

741
01:09:14,900 --> 01:09:18,904
No, I didn't. I was just stretching.

742
01:09:26,453 --> 01:09:28,330
You're taller.

743
01:09:28,872 --> 01:09:30,374
-Who?
-You!

744
01:09:30,582 --> 01:09:32,167
-Than what?
-Than me!

745
01:09:32,668 --> 01:09:34,795
I've always been taller than you.

746
01:09:34,961 --> 01:09:39,591
Pippin, everyone knows I'm the tall one.
You're the short one.

747
01:09:40,425 --> 01:09:41,968
Please, Merry.

748
01:09:42,135 --> 01:09:45,972
You're what? Three-foot-six? At the most?

749
01:09:46,598 --> 01:09:48,725
Whereas me, I'm pushing 3'7".

750
01:09:48,892 --> 01:09:50,602
[ENTISH GROAN]

751
01:09:51,520 --> 01:09:53,772
3'8"!

752
01:09:55,732 --> 01:09:57,609
Three-foot-eight.

753
01:10:00,612 --> 01:10:02,531
You did something.

754
01:10:08,328 --> 01:10:09,913
PIPPIN:
Merry, don't! Don't drink it!

755
01:10:10,831 --> 01:10:12,332
Merry!

756
01:10:12,499 --> 01:10:14,835
No, Treebeard said that you
shouldn't have any.

757
01:10:15,001 --> 01:10:18,922
MERRY: I want some!
-It could well be dangerous!

758
01:10:19,131 --> 01:10:21,258
Give me it back. Merry!

759
01:10:23,135 --> 01:10:24,428
What's happening?!

760
01:10:25,303 --> 01:10:26,763
It's got my leg!

761
01:10:27,139 --> 01:10:28,640
Merry!

762
01:10:31,435 --> 01:10:33,937
[GRUNTING]

763
01:10:37,149 --> 01:10:38,358
No!

764
01:10:47,951 --> 01:10:49,661
PIPPIN:
Help!

765
01:10:56,334 --> 01:10:58,211
TREEBEARD:
Away with you.

766
01:10:58,378 --> 01:11:00,172
You should not be waking.

767
01:11:00,672 --> 01:11:05,677
Eat earth. Dig deep. Drink water.

768
01:11:06,219 --> 01:11:08,805
Go to sleep.

769
01:11:09,181 --> 01:11:10,974
Away with you.

770
01:11:11,183 --> 01:11:14,478
Come, the forest is waking up.

771
01:11:15,020 --> 01:11:16,980
It isn't safe.

772
01:11:19,608 --> 01:11:23,528
The trees have grown wild
and dangerous.

773
01:11:23,695 --> 01:11:26,740
Anger festers in their hearts.

774
01:11:27,574 --> 01:11:29,201
Black are their thoughts.

775
01:11:29,367 --> 01:11:31,912
Strong is their hate.

776
01:11:32,078 --> 01:11:34,831
They will harm you if they can.

777
01:11:34,998 --> 01:11:38,585
There are too few of us now.

778
01:11:38,752 --> 01:11:42,756
Too few of us Ents left to manage them.

779
01:11:43,381 --> 01:11:46,009
Why are there so few of you
when you have lived so long?

780
01:11:46,218 --> 01:11:49,387
-Are there Ent children?
-Bru-ra-hroom.

781
01:11:49,554 --> 01:11:55,185
There have been no Entings
for a terrible long count of years.

782
01:11:55,352 --> 01:12:00,607
-Why is that?
-We lost the Entwives.

783
01:12:00,857 --> 01:12:02,275
Oh, I'm sorry.

784
01:12:02,442 --> 01:12:06,363
-How did they die?
-Die? No.

785
01:12:06,530 --> 01:12:09,783
We lost them.

786
01:12:09,950 --> 01:12:15,038
And now we cannot find them.

787
01:12:15,247 --> 01:12:21,419
I don't suppose you've seen Entwives
in the Shire?

788
01:12:21,586 --> 01:12:24,172
Can't say that I have.

789
01:12:24,673 --> 01:12:26,758
You, Pip?

790
01:12:28,176 --> 01:12:30,554
What do they look like?

791
01:12:33,014 --> 01:12:37,686
I don't remember now.

792
01:12:54,077 --> 01:12:57,998
GANDALF: Edoras and the Golden Hall
of Meduseld.

793
01:12:58,790 --> 01:13:01,418
There dwells Théoden, King of Rohan...

794
01:13:02,085 --> 01:13:05,005
<i>...whose mind is overthrown.</i>

795
01:13:05,171 --> 01:13:09,426
<i>Saruman's hold over King Théoden
is now very strong.</i>

796
01:13:10,093 --> 01:13:13,263
EOWYN:
My lord, your son...

797
01:13:13,430 --> 01:13:15,599
...he is dead.

798
01:13:17,100 --> 01:13:18,935
My lord?

799
01:13:20,186 --> 01:13:21,354
Uncle?

800
01:13:28,153 --> 01:13:30,447
Will you not go to him?

801
01:13:33,533 --> 01:13:35,952
Will you do nothing?

802
01:13:36,119 --> 01:13:38,121
Be careful what you say.

803
01:13:38,330 --> 01:13:40,457
Do not look for welcome here.

804
01:14:04,522 --> 01:14:08,693
Oh, he must have died
sometime in the night.

805
01:14:08,860 --> 01:14:11,029
What a tragedy for the king...

806
01:14:11,237 --> 01:14:14,199
...to lose his only son and heir.

807
01:14:15,367 --> 01:14:19,829
I understand.
His passing is hard to accept.

808
01:14:19,996 --> 01:14:24,918
Especially now that your brother
has deserted you.

809
01:14:25,085 --> 01:14:26,544
Leave me alone, snake!

810
01:14:28,004 --> 01:14:29,673
Oh, but you are alone.

811
01:14:31,299 --> 01:14:36,054
Who knows what you've spoken
to the darkness...

812
01:14:36,221 --> 01:14:39,683
...in the bitter watches of the night...

813
01:14:39,891 --> 01:14:43,520
...when all your life seems to shrink.

814
01:14:43,687 --> 01:14:47,899
The walls of your bower
closing in about you.

815
01:14:48,066 --> 01:14:52,654
A hutch to trammel some wild thing in.

816
01:14:54,906 --> 01:14:56,783
So fair.

817
01:14:58,034 --> 01:14:59,411
80 cold.

818
01:15:01,204 --> 01:15:03,415
Like a morning of pale spring...

819
01:15:03,623 --> 01:15:07,043
...still clinging to winter's chill.

820
01:15:20,807 --> 01:15:23,309
Your words are poison.

821
01:16:55,819 --> 01:16:58,321
You'll find more cheer in a graveyard.

822
01:17:11,543 --> 01:17:12,585
Ah.

823
01:17:12,752 --> 01:17:16,548
I cannot allow you before Théoden King
so armed, Gandalf Greyhame.

824
01:17:18,049 --> 01:17:20,593
By order of Grima Wormtongue.

825
01:17:37,902 --> 01:17:40,905
-Your staff.
-Hm? Oh....

826
01:17:43,074 --> 01:17:46,578
You would not part an old man
from his walking stick.

827
01:18:05,388 --> 01:18:08,266
My lord, Gandalf the Grey is coming.

828
01:18:12,228 --> 01:18:14,022
[DOOR LOCKS]

829
01:18:16,608 --> 01:18:18,193
He's a herald of woe.

830
01:18:18,359 --> 01:18:22,739
The courtesy of your hall
is somewhat lessened of late...

831
01:18:23,865 --> 01:18:25,283
...Théoden King.

832
01:18:25,992 --> 01:18:28,536
He's not welcome.

833
01:18:29,454 --> 01:18:34,751
Why should I welcome you...

834
01:18:35,251 --> 01:18:38,922
...Gandalf Stormcrow?

835
01:18:39,130 --> 01:18:42,425
A just question, my liege.

836
01:18:42,634 --> 01:18:45,428
Late is the hour...

837
01:18:45,637 --> 01:18:49,641
...in which this conjurer
chooses to appear.

838
01:18:50,391 --> 01:18:52,435
Léthspell I name him.

839
01:18:52,644 --> 01:18:55,521
III news is an in guest.

840
01:18:55,688 --> 01:19:00,276
Be silent. Keep your forked tongue
behind your teeth.

841
01:19:00,443 --> 01:19:02,362
I have not passed
through fire and death...

842
01:19:02,528 --> 01:19:05,782
...to bandy crooked words
with a witless worm.

843
01:19:06,741 --> 01:19:08,868
His staff.

844
01:19:09,035 --> 01:19:13,164
I told you to take the Wizard's staff.

845
01:19:16,501 --> 01:19:18,461
Théoden...

846
01:19:19,003 --> 01:19:21,589
...son of Thengel...

847
01:19:23,341 --> 01:19:25,718
...too long have you sat
in the Shadows.

848
01:19:28,680 --> 01:19:31,975
I would stay still if I were you.

849
01:19:32,183 --> 01:19:34,227
Hearken to me!

850
01:19:39,691 --> 01:19:41,859
I release you...

851
01:19:42,026 --> 01:19:43,987
...from the spell.

852
01:19:44,612 --> 01:19:46,990
[LAUGHS]

853
01:19:55,540 --> 01:19:58,584
You have no power here...

854
01:19:58,835 --> 01:20:02,380
...Gandalf the Grey.

855
01:20:07,802 --> 01:20:12,849
I will draw you, Saruman,
as poison is drawn from a wound.

856
01:20:13,099 --> 01:20:15,351
[GROANING]

857
01:20:22,275 --> 01:20:23,818
Wait.

858
01:20:25,236 --> 01:20:29,073
SARUMAN'S VOICE:
If I go, Théoden dies.

859
01:20:29,782 --> 01:20:31,993
You did not kill me...

860
01:20:32,160 --> 01:20:34,370
...you will not kill him.

861
01:20:38,249 --> 01:20:39,959
SARUMAN:
Rohan is mine.

862
01:20:41,461 --> 01:20:42,795
Be gone.

863
01:20:47,467 --> 01:20:50,511
[YELLING]

864
01:21:00,438 --> 01:21:02,315
[GROANS]

865
01:21:27,298 --> 01:21:29,467
I know your face.

866
01:21:34,013 --> 01:21:35,306
Eowyn.

867
01:21:37,600 --> 01:21:38,851
Eowyn.

868
01:21:47,151 --> 01:21:48,319
Gandalf?

869
01:21:48,861 --> 01:21:51,739
Breathe the free air again, my friend.

870
01:22:05,128 --> 01:22:07,713
Dark have been my dreams of late.

871
01:22:11,843 --> 01:22:15,638
Your fingers would remember
their old strength better...

872
01:22:15,847 --> 01:22:18,766
...if they grasped your sword.

873
01:22:56,471 --> 01:22:58,806
[YELLS]

874
01:23:01,058 --> 01:23:02,226
[GROANS]

875
01:23:03,895 --> 01:23:05,897
WORMTONGUE:
I've only...

876
01:23:06,063 --> 01:23:09,108
...ever served you, my lord.

877
01:23:09,275 --> 01:23:14,280
Your Ieechcraft would have had me
crawling on all fours like a beast!

878
01:23:15,281 --> 01:23:17,241
WORMTONGUE:
Send me not from your sight.

879
01:23:19,535 --> 01:23:22,246
ARAGORN:
No, my lord! No, my lord.

880
01:23:22,455 --> 01:23:23,664
Let him go.

881
01:23:24,415 --> 01:23:27,585
Enough blood has been spilt
on his account.

882
01:23:36,719 --> 01:23:39,055
WORMTONGUE:
Get out of my way!

883
01:23:41,265 --> 01:23:44,435
MAN:
Hail, Théoden King!

884
01:24:09,085 --> 01:24:11,629
Where is Théodred?

885
01:24:14,632 --> 01:24:17,134
Where is my son?

886
01:25:05,516 --> 01:25:09,020
[CHANTING IN ROHIRRIM
ANCESTRAL LANGUAGE]

887
01:25:44,388 --> 01:25:46,098
THEODEN:
Simbelmyné.

888
01:25:51,228 --> 01:25:54,857
Ever has it grown on the tombs
of my forebearers.

889
01:25:58,694 --> 01:26:01,656
Now it shall cover the grave
of my son.

890
01:26:03,783 --> 01:26:07,662
Alas that these evil days
should be mine.

891
01:26:08,412 --> 01:26:12,833
The young perish and the old linger.

892
01:26:13,417 --> 01:26:15,544
That I should live...

893
01:26:15,711 --> 01:26:19,090
...to see the last days of my house.

894
01:26:20,299 --> 01:26:24,178
Théodred's death
was not of your making.

895
01:26:27,223 --> 01:26:30,601
No parent should have to bury
their child.

896
01:26:47,326 --> 01:26:49,203
GANDALF:
He was strong in life.

897
01:26:50,287 --> 01:26:53,874
His spirit will find its way
to the halls of your fathers.

898
01:27:04,093 --> 01:27:06,095
[SPEAKING IN ROHIRRIM
ANCESTRAL LANGUAGE]

899
01:27:38,461 --> 01:27:40,337
They had no warning.

900
01:27:40,504 --> 01:27:42,923
They were unarmed.

901
01:27:43,382 --> 01:27:47,428
Now the Wild Men are moving through
the Westfold, burning as they go.

902
01:27:48,345 --> 01:27:50,306
Rick, cot and tree.

903
01:27:50,681 --> 01:27:52,808
-Where is Mama?
EOWYN: Shh.

904
01:27:53,684 --> 01:27:57,855
This is but a taste of the terror
that Saruman will unleash.

905
01:27:58,022 --> 01:28:02,443
All the more potent for he is driven now
by fear of Sauron.

906
01:28:04,028 --> 01:28:07,031
Ride out and meet him head on.

907
01:28:07,782 --> 01:28:11,285
Draw him away from your women
and children.

908
01:28:11,619 --> 01:28:13,245
You must fight.

909
01:28:13,412 --> 01:28:17,249
You have 2000 good men riding north
as we speak.

910
01:28:17,416 --> 01:28:19,043
Eomer is loyal to you.

911
01:28:19,210 --> 01:28:21,921
His men will return
and fight for their king.

912
01:28:22,087 --> 01:28:26,008
They will be 300 leagues from here
by now.

913
01:28:29,720 --> 01:28:31,889
Eomer cannot help us.

914
01:28:32,515 --> 01:28:34,308
I know what it is you want of me...

915
01:28:34,475 --> 01:28:37,728
...but I will not bring further death
to my people.

916
01:28:39,396 --> 01:28:41,106
I will not risk open war.

917
01:28:43,317 --> 01:28:46,737
Open war is upon you,
whether you would risk it or not.

918
01:28:50,950 --> 01:28:52,576
THEODEN:
When last I looked...

919
01:28:53,035 --> 01:28:56,664
...Théoden, not Aragorn,
was king of Rohan.

920
01:29:01,544 --> 01:29:03,128
[BURPS]

921
01:29:03,546 --> 01:29:05,798
Then what is the king's decision?

922
01:29:11,387 --> 01:29:12,763
<i>HAMA:
By order of the king...</i>

923
01:29:12,930 --> 01:29:14,348
...the city must empty.

924
01:29:15,516 --> 01:29:18,394
We make for the refuge of Helm's Deep.

925
01:29:18,686 --> 01:29:22,565
Do not burden yourself with treasures.
Take only what provisions you need.

926
01:29:22,773 --> 01:29:24,275
GIMLI:
Helm's Deep.

927
01:29:24,441 --> 01:29:27,987
They flee to the mountains
when they should stand and fight.

928
01:29:28,153 --> 01:29:30,114
Who will defend them if not their king?

929
01:29:30,281 --> 01:29:32,741
He's only doing what he thinks
is best for his people.

930
01:29:32,908 --> 01:29:34,743
Helm's Deep has saved them
in the past.

931
01:29:34,910 --> 01:29:38,789
There is no way out of that ravine.
Théoden is walking into a trap.

932
01:29:38,956 --> 01:29:41,166
He thinks he's leading them to safety.

933
01:29:41,333 --> 01:29:43,502
What they will get is a massacre.

934
01:29:45,045 --> 01:29:47,548
Théoden has a strong will,
but I fear for him.

935
01:29:48,424 --> 01:29:51,802
I fear for the survival of Rohan.

936
01:29:52,219 --> 01:29:55,097
He will need you before the end,
Aragorn.

937
01:29:55,556 --> 01:29:58,350
The people of Rohan will need you.

938
01:29:58,726 --> 01:30:01,186
The defenses have to hold.

939
01:30:02,605 --> 01:30:04,356
They Will hold.

940
01:30:08,360 --> 01:30:10,654
The Grey Pilgrim.

941
01:30:10,821 --> 01:30:13,449
That's what they used to call me.

942
01:30:13,616 --> 01:30:18,746
Three hundred lives of Men I've walked
this earth, and now I have no time.

943
01:30:20,331 --> 01:30:22,541
With luck, my search will not
be in vain.

944
01:30:23,083 --> 01:30:26,378
Look to my coming at first light
on the fifth day.

945
01:30:27,254 --> 01:30:29,965
At dawn, look to the east.

946
01:30:30,132 --> 01:30:31,675
Go.

947
01:30:45,606 --> 01:30:47,566
[HORSE NEIGHING]

948
01:30:58,994 --> 01:31:02,373
That horse is half mad, my lord.
There's nothing you can do. Leave him.

949
01:31:03,791 --> 01:31:05,876
[ARAGORN SPEAKING IN ELVISH]

950
01:31:41,412 --> 01:31:43,455
His name is Brego.

951
01:31:44,957 --> 01:31:46,917
He was my cousin's horse.

952
01:31:47,084 --> 01:31:48,919
Brego.

953
01:31:50,421 --> 01:31:53,173
[IN ELVISH]
Your name is kingly.

954
01:31:53,632 --> 01:31:55,634
[CONTINUES SPEAKING IN ELVISH]

955
01:32:03,642 --> 01:32:06,061
I have heard of the magic of Elves...

956
01:32:06,228 --> 01:32:09,523
...but I did not look for it
in a Ranger from the North.

957
01:32:10,566 --> 01:32:12,985
You speak as one of their own.

958
01:32:14,778 --> 01:32:17,239
I was raised in Rivendell...

959
01:32:17,489 --> 01:32:19,033
...for a time.

960
01:32:22,327 --> 01:32:24,371
Turn this fellow free.

961
01:32:24,997 --> 01:32:27,499
He's seen enough of war.

962
01:32:39,261 --> 01:32:42,097
Gandalf the White.

963
01:32:42,264 --> 01:32:44,641
Gandalf the Fool!

964
01:32:45,976 --> 01:32:50,230
Does he seek to humble me
with his newfound piety?

965
01:32:51,190 --> 01:32:55,152
WORMTONGUE: There were three
who followed the wizard.

966
01:32:55,569 --> 01:33:00,908
An Elf, a Dwarf and a Man.

967
01:33:01,283 --> 01:33:04,078
You stink of horse.

968
01:33:09,333 --> 01:33:11,210
The Man...

969
01:33:13,253 --> 01:33:17,466
-...was he from Gondor?
-No, from the North.

970
01:33:17,633 --> 01:33:21,428
One of the Dunedain Rangers,
I thought he was.

971
01:33:21,595 --> 01:33:23,388
His cloth was poor.

972
01:33:24,306 --> 01:33:29,436
And yet he bore a strange ring.

973
01:33:30,521 --> 01:33:34,066
Two serpents with emerald eyes.

974
01:33:34,233 --> 01:33:40,072
One devouring,
the other crowned with golden flowers.

975
01:33:40,239 --> 01:33:42,157
SARUMAN:
The Ring of Barahir.

976
01:33:43,117 --> 01:33:46,703
So Gandalf Greyhame
thinks he has found Isildur's heir.

977
01:33:46,870 --> 01:33:50,207
The lost king of Gondor.
He is a fool.

978
01:33:50,374 --> 01:33:53,127
The line was broken years ago.

979
01:33:54,545 --> 01:33:56,004
It matters not.

980
01:33:56,171 --> 01:33:58,715
The world of Men shall fall.

981
01:33:58,882 --> 01:34:00,759
It will begin at Edoras.

982
01:34:09,977 --> 01:34:11,895
I am ready, Gamling.

983
01:34:12,062 --> 01:34:14,565
Bring my horse.

984
01:34:17,693 --> 01:34:19,069
This is not a defeat.

985
01:34:21,488 --> 01:34:22,698
We will return.

986
01:34:28,162 --> 01:34:30,581
We will return.

987
01:34:53,937 --> 01:34:55,898
You have some skill with a blade.

988
01:35:04,406 --> 01:35:06,491
Women of this country learned long ago:

989
01:35:06,658 --> 01:35:09,286
Those without swords
can still die upon them.

990
01:35:09,453 --> 01:35:11,288
I fear neither death nor pain.

991
01:35:12,539 --> 01:35:14,666
What do you fear, my lady?

992
01:35:18,045 --> 01:35:19,880
A cage.

993
01:35:21,173 --> 01:35:25,010
To stay behind bars until use
and old age accept them.

994
01:35:25,177 --> 01:35:29,139
And all chance of valor has gone
beyond recall or desire.

995
01:35:32,517 --> 01:35:34,561
You're a daughter of kings...

996
01:35:35,812 --> 01:35:39,149
...a shieldmaiden of Rohan.

997
01:35:44,404 --> 01:35:46,949
I do not think that would be your fate.

998
01:36:19,982 --> 01:36:23,026
WORMTONGUE:
<i>Théoden Will not stay at Edoras.</i>

999
01:36:23,193 --> 01:36:25,320
It's vulnerable. He knows this.

1000
01:36:25,487 --> 01:36:28,365
He will expect an attack on the city.

1001
01:36:29,700 --> 01:36:32,953
They will flee to Helm's Deep...

1002
01:36:33,120 --> 01:36:35,455
...the great fortress of Rohan.

1003
01:36:36,707 --> 01:36:41,044
<i>It is a dangerous road to take
through the mountains.</i>

1004
01:36:42,504 --> 01:36:44,214
<i>They will be slow.</i>

1005
01:36:44,589 --> 01:36:49,011
They will have women and children
with them.

1006
01:36:52,889 --> 01:36:55,225
Send out your Warg-riders.

1007
01:36:55,726 --> 01:36:59,104
[GROWLING]

1008
01:37:10,032 --> 01:37:12,951
Hey, stinker, don't go getting
too far ahead.

1009
01:37:13,118 --> 01:37:15,787
-Why do you do that?
-What?

1010
01:37:15,954 --> 01:37:18,498
Call him names.
Run him down all the time.

1011
01:37:18,915 --> 01:37:20,959
Because.

1012
01:37:22,502 --> 01:37:24,629
Because that's what he is, Mr. Frodo.

1013
01:37:24,796 --> 01:37:27,007
There's naught left in him
but lies and deceit.

1014
01:37:27,424 --> 01:37:30,218
It's the Ring he wants.
It's all he cares about.

1015
01:37:30,385 --> 01:37:32,637
You have no idea what it did to him...

1016
01:37:32,804 --> 01:37:35,307
...what it's still doing to him.

1017
01:37:37,517 --> 01:37:39,603
I want to help him, <i>Sam.</i>

1018
01:37:39,770 --> 01:37:41,063
Why?

1019
01:37:46,360 --> 01:37:49,488
Because I have to believe
he can come back.

1020
01:37:53,784 --> 01:37:55,660
You can't save him, Mr. Frodo.

1021
01:37:55,827 --> 01:37:58,580
What do you know about it?
Nothing!

1022
01:38:05,504 --> 01:38:09,716
I'm sorry, <i>Sam.</i> I don't know
why I said that.

1023
01:38:10,550 --> 01:38:11,676
I do.

1024
01:38:13,720 --> 01:38:15,597
It's the Ring.

1025
01:38:16,139 --> 01:38:17,724
You can't take your eyes off it.

1026
01:38:18,433 --> 01:38:20,435
I've seen you.

1027
01:38:20,894 --> 01:38:24,731
You're not eating. You barely sleep.

1028
01:38:26,483 --> 01:38:28,735
It's taken hold of you, Mr. Frodo.

1029
01:38:28,902 --> 01:38:31,613
-You have to fight it.
-I know what I have to do, Sam.

1030
01:38:31,822 --> 01:38:34,699
The Ring was entrusted to me.
It's my task.

1031
01:38:34,866 --> 01:38:36,618
Mine! My own!

1032
01:38:37,452 --> 01:38:39,579
Can't you hear yourself?

1033
01:38:39,746 --> 01:38:41,415
Don't you know who you sound like?

1034
01:38:51,675 --> 01:38:53,802
GOLLUM:
We wants it.

1035
01:38:53,969 --> 01:38:56,680
We needs it.

1036
01:38:56,847 --> 01:39:01,643
Must have the precious.

1037
01:39:01,852 --> 01:39:05,272
They stole it from us.

1038
01:39:05,439 --> 01:39:08,817
Sneaky little Hobbitses.

1039
01:39:08,984 --> 01:39:12,863
Wicked. Tricksy. False.

1040
01:39:13,029 --> 01:39:16,324
SMEAGOL:
No. Not master.

1041
01:39:16,491 --> 01:39:20,328
GOLLUM:
Yes, precious. False.

1042
01:39:20,495 --> 01:39:25,000
They will cheat you, hurt you, lie!

1043
01:39:26,126 --> 01:39:28,587
SMEAGOL:
Master's my friend.

1044
01:39:28,753 --> 01:39:33,884
You don't have any friends.
Nobody likes you.

1045
01:39:35,093 --> 01:39:37,596
Not listening. I'm not listening.

1046
01:39:37,762 --> 01:39:41,766
You're a liar and a thief.

1047
01:39:42,392 --> 01:39:43,977
No.

1048
01:39:44,895 --> 01:39:47,772
Murderer.

1049
01:39:50,233 --> 01:39:51,276
Go away.

1050
01:39:51,443 --> 01:39:53,820
Go away?

1051
01:39:55,822 --> 01:39:58,617
I hate you.

1052
01:39:58,783 --> 01:40:01,203
I hate you.

1053
01:40:01,495 --> 01:40:04,789
Where would you be without me?
GOLLUM. GOLLUM.

1054
01:40:04,956 --> 01:40:06,791
I saved us.

1055
01:40:06,958 --> 01:40:11,505
It was me. We survived because of me.

1056
01:40:12,714 --> 01:40:16,301
Not anymore.

1057
01:40:17,636 --> 01:40:19,221
What did you say?

1058
01:40:21,264 --> 01:40:25,101
Master looks after us now.

1059
01:40:25,268 --> 01:40:28,772
We don't need you.

1060
01:40:29,481 --> 01:40:31,066
What?

1061
01:40:31,233 --> 01:40:32,984
Leave now...

1062
01:40:33,151 --> 01:40:36,947
...and never come back.

1063
01:40:37,113 --> 01:40:38,156
No.

1064
01:40:38,657 --> 01:40:42,869
Leave now and never come back.

1065
01:40:45,455 --> 01:40:51,378
Leave now and never come back!

1066
01:41:03,348 --> 01:41:06,059
We told him to go away.

1067
01:41:06,226 --> 01:41:09,187
And away he goes, precious.

1068
01:41:09,354 --> 01:41:11,356
Gone! Gone! Gone!

1069
01:41:11,523 --> 01:41:13,316
Sméagol is free!

1070
01:41:18,238 --> 01:41:19,739
SMEAGOL:
Look.

1071
01:41:19,906 --> 01:41:24,411
Look. See what Sméagol finds?

1072
01:41:24,744 --> 01:41:27,914
[CHUCKLING]

1073
01:41:33,920 --> 01:41:35,338
They are young.

1074
01:41:35,505 --> 01:41:38,049
They are tender. They are nice.

1075
01:41:38,216 --> 01:41:41,761
Yes, they are. Eat them. Eat them!

1076
01:41:44,514 --> 01:41:46,057
You'll make him sick, you will...

1077
01:41:47,267 --> 01:41:49,519
...behaving like that.

1078
01:41:51,855 --> 01:41:54,649
There's only one way to eat
a brace of coneys.

1079
01:41:55,150 --> 01:41:57,277
[SMEAGOL SHRIEKING]

1080
01:41:58,820 --> 01:42:00,405
What's it doing?

1081
01:42:01,114 --> 01:42:03,783
Stupid, fat Hobbit.

1082
01:42:03,950 --> 01:42:06,161
It ruins it.

1083
01:42:06,328 --> 01:42:09,956
What's to ruin? There's hardly any meat
on them.

1084
01:42:10,624 --> 01:42:13,585
[BIRD WHISTLING]

1085
01:42:14,085 --> 01:42:16,671
What we need is a few good taters.

1086
01:42:17,547 --> 01:42:20,592
What's taters, precious?

1087
01:42:20,759 --> 01:42:22,510
What's taters? Eh?

1088
01:42:22,677 --> 01:42:24,387
Po-ta-toes.

1089
01:42:24,721 --> 01:42:27,974
Boil them, mash them,
stick them in a stew.

1090
01:42:29,476 --> 01:42:34,981
Lovely, big, golden chips
with a nice piece of fried fish.

1091
01:42:36,274 --> 01:42:38,193
Even you couldn't say no to that.

1092
01:42:38,568 --> 01:42:40,695
Oh, yes, we could.

1093
01:42:40,862 --> 01:42:44,366
Spoil a nice fish.

1094
01:42:45,659 --> 01:42:48,286
Give it to us raw...

1095
01:42:48,453 --> 01:42:51,498
...and wriggling.

1096
01:42:51,665 --> 01:42:54,793
You keep nasty chips.

1097
01:42:55,710 --> 01:42:57,796
You're hopeless.

1098
01:43:10,308 --> 01:43:11,810
Mr. Frodo?

1099
01:43:29,703 --> 01:43:32,372
SAM: Who are they?
SMEAGOL: Wicked Men.

1100
01:43:32,539 --> 01:43:34,999
Servants of Sauron.

1101
01:43:35,792 --> 01:43:38,002
They are called to Mordor.

1102
01:43:38,169 --> 01:43:41,214
The Dark One is gathering all armies
to him.

1103
01:43:41,381 --> 01:43:44,551
It won't be long now.
He will soon be ready.

1104
01:43:46,136 --> 01:43:49,764
-Ready to do what?
-To make his war.

1105
01:43:49,931 --> 01:43:55,145
The last war that will cover
all the world in Shadow.

1106
01:43:55,395 --> 01:43:57,230
We've got to get moving. Come on, Sam.

1107
01:43:57,397 --> 01:43:58,440
[OLIPHAUNT GROANS]

1108
01:43:58,648 --> 01:43:59,858
Mr. Frodo.

1109
01:44:00,358 --> 01:44:01,985
Look.

1110
01:44:05,655 --> 01:44:07,949
It's an oliphaunt.

1111
01:44:09,659 --> 01:44:12,537
[GROANING]

1112
01:44:16,166 --> 01:44:19,169
No one at home will believe this.

1113
01:44:23,423 --> 01:44:25,884
[BIRD WHISTLES]

1114
01:44:30,305 --> 01:44:32,182
Sméagol?

1115
01:44:34,934 --> 01:44:37,145
[ARROWS FLYING]

1116
01:44:37,312 --> 01:44:38,897
[SCREAMING]

1117
01:44:49,824 --> 01:44:51,951
[OLIPHAUNTS TRUMPETING]

1118
01:45:12,514 --> 01:45:15,016
We've lingered here too long.

1119
01:45:18,019 --> 01:45:19,354
Come on, <i>Sam.</i>

1120
01:45:31,407 --> 01:45:32,659
No!

1121
01:45:32,826 --> 01:45:36,996
-Wait! We're innocent travelers!
-Travelers?

1122
01:45:37,247 --> 01:45:42,335
There are no travelers in this land.
Only servants of the Dark Tower.

1123
01:45:42,502 --> 01:45:45,380
We are bound to an errand of secrecy.

1124
01:45:46,756 --> 01:45:50,134
Those that claim to oppose the enemy
would do well not to hinder us.

1125
01:45:50,301 --> 01:45:52,387
The enemy?

1126
01:45:54,430 --> 01:45:57,934
His sense of duty was no less
than yours, I deem.

1127
01:46:00,395 --> 01:46:02,522
You wonder what his name is...

1128
01:46:04,023 --> 01:46:06,276
...where he came from.

1129
01:46:08,278 --> 01:46:10,697
And if he was really evil at heart.

1130
01:46:12,365 --> 01:46:15,827
What lies or threats led him
on this long march from home.

1131
01:46:17,412 --> 01:46:19,914
If he would not rather have stayed there...

1132
01:46:22,083 --> 01:46:23,626
...in peace.

1133
01:46:27,171 --> 01:46:30,216
War will make corpses of us all.

1134
01:46:30,383 --> 01:46:32,427
Bind their hands.

1135
01:46:42,014 --> 01:46:44,767
GIMLI: It's true, you don't see
many Dwarf women.

1136
01:46:44,975 --> 01:46:48,604
And in fact, they are so alike
in voice and appearance...

1137
01:46:48,771 --> 01:46:51,982
...that they're often mistaken
for Dwarf men.

1138
01:46:52,316 --> 01:46:54,234
It's the beards.

1139
01:46:54,485 --> 01:46:56,570
This, in turn, has given rise
to the belief...

1140
01:46:56,737 --> 01:46:59,615
...that there are no Dwarf women...

1141
01:46:59,782 --> 01:47:04,036
...and that Dwarves just spring out
of holes in the ground...

1142
01:47:05,704 --> 01:47:07,081
...which is, of course, ridiculous.

1143
01:47:07,247 --> 01:47:08,707
[YELLS]

1144
01:47:13,670 --> 01:47:16,006
GIMLI:
It's all right. Nobody panic.

1145
01:47:16,382 --> 01:47:18,384
That was deliberate.
It was deliberate.

1146
01:47:20,302 --> 01:47:24,139
I haven't seen my niece smile
for a long time.

1147
01:47:24,431 --> 01:47:27,184
She was a girl when they brought
her father back dead.

1148
01:47:27,351 --> 01:47:29,645
Cut down by Orcs.

1149
01:47:29,812 --> 01:47:32,815
She watched her mother
succumb to grief.

1150
01:47:33,440 --> 01:47:38,153
Then she was left alone,
to tend her king in growing fear.

1151
01:47:38,320 --> 01:47:42,866
Doomed to wait upon an old man,
who should have loved her as a father.

1152
01:47:52,835 --> 01:47:55,212
Gimli.

1153
01:47:55,379 --> 01:47:57,464
No, I couldn't.

1154
01:47:57,631 --> 01:47:59,466
I really couldn't.

1155
01:48:03,971 --> 01:48:05,597
I made some stew.

1156
01:48:05,764 --> 01:48:09,059
It isn't much, but it's hot.

1157
01:48:16,859 --> 01:48:18,902
Thank you.

1158
01:48:39,423 --> 01:48:41,967
-It's good.
-Really?

1159
01:48:45,929 --> 01:48:49,308
My uncle told me a strange thing.

1160
01:48:50,601 --> 01:48:54,688
He said that you rode to war
with Thengel, my grandfather.

1161
01:48:55,105 --> 01:48:57,608
But he must be mistaken.

1162
01:48:57,816 --> 01:49:02,237
King Théoden has a good memory.
He was only a small child at the time.

1163
01:49:03,363 --> 01:49:06,617
Then you must be at least 60.

1164
01:49:08,660 --> 01:49:10,245
Seventy?

1165
01:49:10,662 --> 01:49:12,331
But you cannot be 80!

1166
01:49:15,667 --> 01:49:17,044
Eighty-seven.

1167
01:49:20,130 --> 01:49:22,257
You are one of the Dunedain.

1168
01:49:23,300 --> 01:49:26,428
A descendant of Numenor,
blessed with long life.

1169
01:49:27,638 --> 01:49:30,265
It was said that your race
had passed into legend.

1170
01:49:30,933 --> 01:49:32,684
There are few of us left.

1171
01:49:32,851 --> 01:49:35,687
The Northern Kingdom
was destroyed long ago.

1172
01:49:36,438 --> 01:49:39,858
I'm sorry. Please, eat.

1173
01:49:54,498 --> 01:49:58,669
ARWEN: <i>The light of the Evenstar
does not wax and wane.</i>

1174
01:49:59,419 --> 01:50:02,881
<i>It is mine to give to whom I will.</i>

1175
01:50:04,675 --> 01:50:07,094
<i>Like my heart.</i>

1176
01:50:08,512 --> 01:50:11,223
<i>Go to sleep.</i>

1177
01:50:11,390 --> 01:50:13,892
I am asleep.

1178
01:50:20,357 --> 01:50:22,317
This is a dream.

1179
01:50:24,528 --> 01:50:27,739
Then it is a good dream.

1180
01:50:39,751 --> 01:50:41,837
Sleep.

1181
01:51:06,903 --> 01:51:08,447
[IN ELVISH]
You told me once...

1182
01:51:10,866 --> 01:51:13,076
this day would come.

1183
01:51:14,077 --> 01:51:16,705
[IN ELVISH]
This is not the end...it is the beginning.

1184
01:51:16,872 --> 01:51:19,041
You must go with Frodo.

1185
01:51:19,750 --> 01:51:21,877
That is your path.

1186
01:51:32,220 --> 01:51:34,931
My path is hidden from me.

1187
01:51:35,641 --> 01:51:39,227
It is already laid before your feet.

1188
01:51:39,394 --> 01:51:42,731
<i>YO“ cannot faker “OW.</i>

1189
01:51:44,816 --> 01:51:46,735
[IN ENGLISH]
Arwen....

1190
01:51:49,237 --> 01:51:51,531
If you trust nothing else...

1191
01:51:51,907 --> 01:51:53,950
trust this...

1192
01:51:55,160 --> 01:51:57,245
trust US.

1193
01:52:36,201 --> 01:52:38,036
EOWYN:
Where is she?

1194
01:52:39,204 --> 01:52:41,623
The woman who gave you that jewel.

1195
01:52:44,960 --> 01:52:47,713
<i>ELROND'.
Our time here is ending.</i>

1196
01:52:48,380 --> 01:52:50,966
Arwen's time is ending.

1197
01:52:51,675 --> 01:52:52,968
Let her go.

1198
01:52:53,135 --> 01:52:55,137
Let her take the ship into the west.

1199
01:52:55,303 --> 01:52:58,390
Let her bear away her love for you
to the Undying Lands.

1200
01:52:58,557 --> 01:53:00,350
There it will be ever green.

1201
01:53:01,852 --> 01:53:04,229
But never more than memory.

1202
01:53:05,480 --> 01:53:08,525
I will not leave my daughter here
to die.

1203
01:53:08,734 --> 01:53:12,362
-She stays because she still has hope.
-She stays for you.

1204
01:53:12,529 --> 01:53:14,865
She belongs with her people.

1205
01:53:27,294 --> 01:53:30,213
[IN ELVISH]
Is this how you would take your leave?

1206
01:53:30,380 --> 01:53:33,550
Did you think you could slip away at
first light - unnoticed?

1207
01:53:36,386 --> 01:53:38,680
[IN ELVISH]
I will not be coming back.

1208
01:53:39,639 --> 01:53:41,433
You underestimate your skill in battle.

1209
01:53:41,600 --> 01:53:43,059
You will come back.

1210
01:53:43,226 --> 01:53:45,270
It is not of death in battle that I speak.

1211
01:53:45,437 --> 01:53:47,856
What do you speak of?

1212
01:53:53,069 --> 01:53:56,156
You have a chance for another life...

1213
01:53:58,116 --> 01:54:02,662
away from war...grief...despair.

1214
01:54:03,163 --> 01:54:04,998
[IN ENGLISH]
Why are you saying this?

1215
01:54:06,583 --> 01:54:09,753
[IN ENGLISH]
I am mortal. You are Elf-kind.

1216
01:54:11,213 --> 01:54:13,882
It was a dream, Arwen.

1217
01:54:14,299 --> 01:54:15,675
Nothing more.

1218
01:54:17,052 --> 01:54:20,263
I don't believe you.

1219
01:54:29,272 --> 01:54:31,107
This belongs to you.

1220
01:54:33,860 --> 01:54:35,445
It was a gift.

1221
01:54:38,114 --> 01:54:39,616
Keep it.

1222
01:54:42,118 --> 01:54:43,328
EOWYN:
My lord?

1223
01:54:46,122 --> 01:54:50,710
She is sailing to the Undying Lands
with all that is left of her kin.

1224
01:55:12,399 --> 01:55:13,692
[HORSE NEIGHS]

1225
01:55:14,150 --> 01:55:15,652
What is it?

1226
01:55:17,153 --> 01:55:19,197
-Héma?
-I'm not sure.

1227
01:55:24,828 --> 01:55:27,664
[YELLING AND ROARING]

1228
01:55:35,755 --> 01:55:37,841
Wargs!

1229
01:55:50,353 --> 01:55:52,022
A scout!

1230
01:55:58,361 --> 01:56:00,864
-What is it? What do you see?
-Warg! We're under attack!

1231
01:56:02,198 --> 01:56:04,409
Get them out of here!

1232
01:56:09,164 --> 01:56:11,207
All riders to the head of the column.

1233
01:56:11,875 --> 01:56:13,877
GIMLI:
Come on. Get me up here. I'm a rider.

1234
01:56:14,044 --> 01:56:15,795
Come on!

1235
01:56:17,756 --> 01:56:20,967
[WARGS BARKING]

1236
01:56:27,599 --> 01:56:30,060
You must lead the people
to Helm's Deep, and make haste.

1237
01:56:30,226 --> 01:56:31,728
-I can fight.
-No!

1238
01:56:34,397 --> 01:56:36,483
You must do this, for me.

1239
01:56:38,485 --> 01:56:40,070
Follow me! Hyah!

1240
01:56:43,573 --> 01:56:47,911
GIMLI: Forward. I mean, charge forward.
EOWYN: Make for the lower ground!

1241
01:56:48,078 --> 01:56:50,747
-That's it! Go on!
-Stay together!

1242
01:58:02,986 --> 01:58:05,280
GIMLI:
Bring your pretty face to my ax.

1243
01:58:08,074 --> 01:58:09,659
That one counts as mine!

1244
01:58:26,342 --> 01:58:27,969
Stinking creature.

1245
01:58:33,058 --> 01:58:34,684
[SNIFFS]

1246
01:58:37,979 --> 01:58:40,023
[GRUNTING]

1247
01:59:39,916 --> 01:59:41,334
[YELLS]

1248
01:59:55,223 --> 01:59:57,100
Aragorn!

1249
02:00:01,813 --> 02:00:03,273
Aragorn?

1250
02:00:09,112 --> 02:00:11,865
[LAUGHING]

1251
02:00:17,287 --> 02:00:20,206
Tell me what happened
and I will ease your passing.

1252
02:00:20,373 --> 02:00:21,791
He's...

1253
02:00:22,375 --> 02:00:23,960
<i>...dead.</i>

1254
02:00:24,627 --> 02:00:27,505
He took a little tumble off the cliff.

1255
02:00:31,134 --> 02:00:32,427
You lie.

1256
02:00:32,927 --> 02:00:35,346
[CHOKES]

1257
02:01:06,336 --> 02:01:07,962
Get the wounded on horses.

1258
02:01:09,255 --> 02:01:12,425
The wolves of Isengard will return.

1259
02:01:12,842 --> 02:01:14,969
Leave the dead.

1260
02:01:22,352 --> 02:01:23,853
Come.

1261
02:01:34,030 --> 02:01:35,657
WOMAN 1: At last!
WOMAN 2: Helm's Deep.

1262
02:01:35,823 --> 02:01:38,701
WOMAN 3:
There it is, Helm's Deep.

1263
02:01:41,246 --> 02:01:43,081
WOMAN 4:
We're safe!

1264
02:01:44,582 --> 02:01:47,460
We're safe, my lady.

1265
02:01:47,627 --> 02:01:48,836
Thank you.

1266
02:02:33,172 --> 02:02:34,590
FREDA: Mama!
MORWEN: Eothain!

1267
02:02:34,757 --> 02:02:36,301
Freda!

1268
02:02:42,056 --> 02:02:44,892
-Where is the rest?
-This is all we could save, my lady.

1269
02:02:48,730 --> 02:02:50,064
Take it to the caves.

1270
02:02:50,231 --> 02:02:53,067
MAN:
Make way for the king.

1271
02:02:54,944 --> 02:02:57,905
GAMLING: Make way for Théoden.
Make way for the king.

1272
02:03:05,788 --> 02:03:09,542
So few. 80 few of you have returned.

1273
02:03:12,295 --> 02:03:14,589
Our people are safe.

1274
02:03:15,923 --> 02:03:18,468
We have paid for it with many lives.

1275
02:03:19,302 --> 02:03:20,845
GIMLI:
My lady.

1276
02:03:24,557 --> 02:03:26,809
Lord Aragorn...

1277
02:03:26,976 --> 02:03:28,227
...where is he?

1278
02:03:30,229 --> 02:03:31,773
He fell.

1279
02:03:54,462 --> 02:03:57,423
Draw all our forces behind the wall.

1280
02:03:57,590 --> 02:04:00,510
Bar the gate.
And set a watch on the surround.

1281
02:04:00,760 --> 02:04:03,846
GAMLING: What of those who cannot fight,
my lord? The women and children?

1282
02:04:04,013 --> 02:04:06,641
THEODEN:
Get them into the caves.

1283
02:04:07,517 --> 02:04:12,355
Saruman's arm will have grown long
indeed if he thinks he can reach us here.

1284
02:04:14,399 --> 02:04:17,819
WORMTONGUE:
<i>Helm's Deep has one weakness.</i>

1285
02:04:17,985 --> 02:04:20,321
<i>Its outer wall is solid rock...</i>

1286
02:04:20,488 --> 02:04:23,574
<i>...but for a small culvert
at its base...</i>

1287
02:04:23,741 --> 02:04:26,536
<i>...which is little more than a drain.</i>

1288
02:04:29,372 --> 02:04:33,543
How? How can fire undo stone?

1289
02:04:33,709 --> 02:04:38,256
What kind of device
could bring down the wall?

1290
02:04:41,884 --> 02:04:45,888
SARUMAN: If the wall is breached,
Helm's Deep will fall.

1291
02:04:46,055 --> 02:04:49,559
Even if it is breached, it would take
a number beyond reckoning...

1292
02:04:49,725 --> 02:04:52,311
...thousands, to storm the Keep.

1293
02:04:52,478 --> 02:04:53,896
SARUMAN:
Tens of thousands.

1294
02:04:54,063 --> 02:04:58,151
WORMTONGUE:
But, my lord, there is no such force.

1295
02:04:58,317 --> 02:05:00,111
[HORNS SOUNDING]

1296
02:05:00,403 --> 02:05:03,781
[ARMY CHEERING]

1297
02:05:10,079 --> 02:05:13,166
A new power is rising.

1298
02:05:13,332 --> 02:05:16,335
Its victory is at hand.

1299
02:05:22,008 --> 02:05:24,093
This night...

1300
02:05:24,510 --> 02:05:28,848
...the land will be stained
with the blood of Rohan!

1301
02:05:29,015 --> 02:05:32,351
March to Helm's Deep!

1302
02:05:32,518 --> 02:05:36,022
Leave none alive!

1303
02:05:38,524 --> 02:05:41,027
To war!

1304
02:05:44,947 --> 02:05:49,410
There will be no dawn for Men.

1305
02:06:06,594 --> 02:06:08,638
Look. There's smoke to the south.

1306
02:06:08,804 --> 02:06:11,974
There is always smoke rising...

1307
02:06:12,183 --> 02:06:16,020
...from Isengard these days.

1308
02:06:16,270 --> 02:06:17,855
Isengard?

1309
02:06:18,064 --> 02:06:19,941
TREEBEARD:
There was a time...

1310
02:06:20,274 --> 02:06:23,819
...when Saruman would walk in my woods.

1311
02:06:23,986 --> 02:06:27,323
But now he has a mind of metal...

1312
02:06:27,990 --> 02:06:30,451
...and wheels.

1313
02:06:31,202 --> 02:06:35,706
He no longer cares for growing things.

1314
02:06:35,873 --> 02:06:37,667
What is it?

1315
02:06:42,672 --> 02:06:44,882
It's Saruman's army.

1316
02:06:45,049 --> 02:06:46,634
The war has started.

1317
02:07:24,922 --> 02:07:29,302
ARWEN: <i>May the grace of the Valar
protect you.</i>

1318
02:08:01,584 --> 02:08:03,461
Brego.

1319
02:08:29,570 --> 02:08:30,738
ELROND:
Arwen.

1320
02:08:32,073 --> 02:08:33,949
[IN ELVISH]
It is time.

1321
02:08:35,993 --> 02:08:39,872
The ships are leaving for Valinor.
Go now... before it is too late.

1322
02:08:40,623 --> 02:08:42,416
I have made my choice.

1323
02:08:48,839 --> 02:08:51,717
[IN ENGLISH]
He is not coming back.

1324
02:08:53,135 --> 02:08:56,472
Why do you linger here
when there is no hope?

1325
02:08:57,390 --> 02:09:00,393
There is still hope.

1326
02:09:04,522 --> 02:09:08,317
If Aragorn survives this war,
you will still be parted.

1327
02:09:11,696 --> 02:09:14,657
If Sauron is defeated
and Aragorn made king...

1328
02:09:14,824 --> 02:09:17,326
...and all that you hope for
comes true...

1329
02:09:17,493 --> 02:09:22,206
...you will still have to taste
the bitterness of mortality.

1330
02:09:22,498 --> 02:09:25,501
Whether by the sword
or the slow decay of time...

1331
02:09:25,668 --> 02:09:28,587
...Aragorn will die.

1332
02:09:31,424 --> 02:09:34,009
<i>And there will be no comfort
for you...</i>

1333
02:09:34,176 --> 02:09:38,389
<i>...no comfort to ease the pain
Of his passing.</i>

1334
02:09:41,183 --> 02:09:43,936
<i>He will come to death...</i>

1335
02:09:44,103 --> 02:09:46,689
<i>...an image of the splendor
Of the kings of Men...</i>

1336
02:09:46,856 --> 02:09:51,527
<i>...in glory undimmed before
the breaking of the world.</i>

1337
02:10:00,619 --> 02:10:04,582
<i>But you, my daughter...</i>

1338
02:10:05,374 --> 02:10:10,421
<i>...you will linger on in darkness
and in doubt...</i>

1339
02:10:10,588 --> 02:10:14,675
<i>...as nightfall in winter
that comes without a star.</i>

1340
02:10:17,052 --> 02:10:19,472
<i>Here you will dwell...</i>

1341
02:10:19,638 --> 02:10:24,560
<i>...bound to your grief
under the fading trees...</i>

1342
02:10:26,270 --> 02:10:28,272
<i>...until all the world is changed...</i>

1343
02:10:28,439 --> 02:10:32,943
...and the long years of your life
are utterly spent.

1344
02:10:41,494 --> 02:10:42,661
Arwen.

1345
02:10:49,293 --> 02:10:51,587
There is nothing for you here...

1346
02:10:52,254 --> 02:10:54,340
...only death.

1347
02:11:15,110 --> 02:11:18,280
[IN ELVISH]
Do I not also have your love?

1348
02:11:19,865 --> 02:11:21,617
[IN ELVISH]
You have my love, father.

1349
02:12:12,877 --> 02:12:16,046
[GALADRIEL SPEAKING IN ELVISH]

1350
02:12:27,766 --> 02:12:31,395
GALADRIEL <i>[IN</i> ENGLISH]: <i>The power of the enemy is growing.</i>

1351
02:12:31,562 --> 02:12:34,189
<i>Sauron will use his puppet,
Saruman...</i>

1352
02:12:34,356 --> 02:12:37,818
<i>...to destroy the people of Rohan.</i>

1353
02:12:39,862 --> 02:12:43,532
<i>lsengard has been unleashed.</i>

1354
02:12:47,828 --> 02:12:51,206
<i>The Eye of Sauron now turns
to Gondor...</i>

1355
02:12:52,333 --> 02:12:55,336
<i>...the last free kingdom of Men.</i>

1356
02:12:55,502 --> 02:12:59,882
<i>His war on this country
will come swiftly.</i>

1357
02:13:03,594 --> 02:13:06,722
<i>He senses the Ring is close.</i>

1358
02:13:06,889 --> 02:13:10,351
<i>The strength of the Ring-bearer
is failing.</i>

1359
02:13:10,517 --> 02:13:14,563
<i>In his heart, Frodo begins
to understand...</i>

1360
02:13:16,106 --> 02:13:19,985
...the quest will claim his life.

1361
02:13:20,152 --> 02:13:22,321
You know this.

1362
02:13:22,905 --> 02:13:25,741
<i>You have foreseen it.</i>

1363
02:13:27,868 --> 02:13:31,330
<i>It is the risk we all took.</i>

1364
02:13:35,709 --> 02:13:39,922
<i>In the gathering dark, the will
of the Ring grows strong.</i>

1365
02:13:41,090 --> 02:13:45,511
<i>It works hard now to find its way back
into the hands of Men.</i>

1366
02:13:45,678 --> 02:13:51,141
<i>Men, who are so easily seduced
by its power.</i>

1367
02:13:51,350 --> 02:13:54,937
<i>The young captain of Gondor
has but to extend his hand...</i>

1368
02:13:55,104 --> 02:13:59,191
<i>...take the Ring for his own,
and the world will fall.</i>

1369
02:14:01,610 --> 02:14:03,445
<i>It is close now.</i>

1370
02:14:03,612 --> 02:14:07,866
<i>So close to achieving its goal.</i>

1371
02:14:08,742 --> 02:14:10,661
[ROARING]

1372
02:14:10,953 --> 02:14:14,623
<i>For Sauron will have dominion
over all life on this Earth...</i>

1373
02:14:14,790 --> 02:14:18,919
<i>...even unto the ending
of the world.</i>

1374
02:14:20,754 --> 02:14:22,589
<i>The time of the Elves...</i>

1375
02:14:22,798 --> 02:14:24,717
<i>...is over.</i>

1376
02:14:25,551 --> 02:14:29,138
<i>Do we leave Middle-earth
to its fate?</i>

1377
02:14:31,098 --> 02:14:34,351
<i>Do we let them stand alone?</i>

1378
02:14:38,981 --> 02:14:40,315
What news?

1379
02:14:40,482 --> 02:14:43,318
Our scouts report Saruman
has attacked Rohan.

1380
02:14:43,485 --> 02:14:46,321
Théoden's people have fled
to Helm's Deep.

1381
02:14:46,488 --> 02:14:50,534
But we must look to our own borders.
Faramir, Orcs are on the move.

1382
02:14:50,701 --> 02:14:53,120
Sauron is marshaling an army.

1383
02:14:53,454 --> 02:14:55,581
Easterlings and Southrons
are at the Black Gate.

1384
02:14:55,748 --> 02:14:59,168
-How many?
-Some thousands. More come every day.

1385
02:15:00,252 --> 02:15:03,839
-Who's covering the river to the north?
-We pulled 500 men at Osgiliath.

1386
02:15:04,006 --> 02:15:07,051
If their city is attacked,
we won't hold it.

1387
02:15:09,178 --> 02:15:11,346
FARAMIR:
Saruman attacks from Isengard.

1388
02:15:11,513 --> 02:15:14,224
Sauron from Mordor.

1389
02:15:15,517 --> 02:15:18,771
The fight will come to Men
on both fronts.

1390
02:15:18,937 --> 02:15:20,647
Gondor is weak.

1391
02:15:20,814 --> 02:15:23,942
Sauron will strike us soon.

1392
02:15:24,693 --> 02:15:26,528
And he will strike hard.

1393
02:15:26,987 --> 02:15:31,075
He knows now we do not have
the strength to repel him.

1394
02:15:45,005 --> 02:15:47,216
My men tell me that you are Orc spies.

1395
02:15:47,382 --> 02:15:50,135
Spies? Now wait just a minute.

1396
02:15:50,302 --> 02:15:52,554
Well, if you're not spies,
then who are you?

1397
02:15:59,436 --> 02:16:01,188
Speak.

1398
02:16:02,272 --> 02:16:04,900
We are Hobbits of the Shire.

1399
02:16:05,234 --> 02:16:08,237
Frodo Baggins is my name,
and this is Samwise Gamgee.

1400
02:16:08,654 --> 02:16:10,197
Your bodyguard?

1401
02:16:10,364 --> 02:16:12,157
His gardener.

1402
02:16:12,741 --> 02:16:14,743
And where is your skulking friend?

1403
02:16:16,245 --> 02:16:18,580
That gangrel creature.

1404
02:16:18,914 --> 02:16:20,874
He had an ill-favored look.

1405
02:16:22,584 --> 02:16:24,503
There was no other.

1406
02:16:28,590 --> 02:16:30,926
We set out from Rivendell
with seven companions.

1407
02:16:34,263 --> 02:16:37,349
One we lost in Moria...

1408
02:16:38,433 --> 02:16:39,935
...two were my kin...

1409
02:16:40,102 --> 02:16:43,856
...a Dwarf there was also.
And an Elf and two Men.

1410
02:16:44,022 --> 02:16:47,943
Aragorn, son of Arathorn,
and Boromir of Gondor.

1411
02:16:52,948 --> 02:16:54,700
You're a friend of Boromir?

1412
02:16:57,119 --> 02:16:58,620
Yes.

1413
02:16:59,705 --> 02:17:00,789
For my part.

1414
02:17:07,296 --> 02:17:10,257
It will grieve you then to learn
that he is dead.

1415
02:17:12,301 --> 02:17:13,760
Dead?

1416
02:17:13,927 --> 02:17:15,971
How? When?

1417
02:17:16,221 --> 02:17:18,891
As one of his companions,
I'd hoped you would tell me.

1418
02:17:19,183 --> 02:17:23,020
If something has happened to Boromir,
we would have you tell us.

1419
02:17:25,772 --> 02:17:32,237
His horn washed up upon the riverbank,
about six days past.

1420
02:17:32,446 --> 02:17:35,532
It was cloven in two.

1421
02:17:37,201 --> 02:17:40,621
But more than this, I know it in my heart.

1422
02:17:42,664 --> 02:17:44,458
He was my brother.

1423
02:18:31,171 --> 02:18:33,173
[MEN CHEERING]

1424
02:18:33,340 --> 02:18:36,385
MEN:
Boromir!

1425
02:18:36,885 --> 02:18:38,762
Boromir!

1426
02:18:43,016 --> 02:18:46,770
This city was once the jewel
of our kingdom.

1427
02:18:46,937 --> 02:18:50,607
A place of light and beauty and music.

1428
02:18:50,774 --> 02:18:53,110
And so it shall be once more!

1429
02:18:55,654 --> 02:18:58,323
Let the armies of Mordor know this:

1430
02:18:58,490 --> 02:19:02,869
Never again will the land of my people
fall into enemy hands.

1431
02:19:06,665 --> 02:19:12,337
This city of Osgiliath
has been reclaimed for Gondor!

1432
02:19:12,713 --> 02:19:14,673
-For Gondor!
-For Gondor!

1433
02:19:14,840 --> 02:19:17,676
-For Gondor!
-For Gondor!

1434
02:19:26,393 --> 02:19:29,146
Good speech. Nice and short.

1435
02:19:29,313 --> 02:19:32,232
Leaves more time for drinking!

1436
02:19:32,524 --> 02:19:36,778
Break out the ale! These men are thirsty!

1437
02:19:40,240 --> 02:19:42,409
Remember today, little brother.

1438
02:19:42,576 --> 02:19:45,579
Today, life is good.

1439
02:19:49,750 --> 02:19:51,335
What?

1440
02:19:51,710 --> 02:19:53,170
He's here.

1441
02:19:56,381 --> 02:19:59,426
-Moment of peace, can he not give us that?
DENETHOR: Where is he?

1442
02:19:59,593 --> 02:20:03,055
Where is Gondor's finest?
Where's my first-born?

1443
02:20:03,597 --> 02:20:05,307
Father!

1444
02:20:10,145 --> 02:20:12,522
They say you vanquished the enemy
almost single-handedly.

1445
02:20:12,689 --> 02:20:16,109
They exaggerate.
The victory belongs to Faramir also.

1446
02:20:17,569 --> 02:20:20,489
But for Faramir, this city
would still be standing.

1447
02:20:21,281 --> 02:20:23,575
Were you not entrusted to protect it?

1448
02:20:23,742 --> 02:20:25,786
I would have done,
but our numbers were too few.

1449
02:20:25,952 --> 02:20:27,662
Oh, too few.

1450
02:20:28,163 --> 02:20:30,540
You let the enemy walk in
and take it on a whim.

1451
02:20:32,751 --> 02:20:35,837
Always you cast a poor reflection on me.

1452
02:20:36,004 --> 02:20:38,256
That is not my intent.

1453
02:20:38,423 --> 02:20:42,177
You give him no credit,
and yet he tries to do your will.

1454
02:20:45,555 --> 02:20:48,475
-He loves you, Father.
-Do not trouble me with Faramir...

1455
02:20:48,642 --> 02:20:51,395
...I know his uses, and they are few.

1456
02:20:51,561 --> 02:20:55,190
We have more urgent things to speak of.

1457
02:20:56,358 --> 02:20:58,777
Elrond of Rivendell has called a meeting.

1458
02:20:58,944 --> 02:21:01,822
He will not say why,
but I have guessed its purpose.

1459
02:21:01,988 --> 02:21:05,784
It is rumored that the weapon
of the enemy has been found.

1460
02:21:07,994 --> 02:21:10,288
The One Ring.

1461
02:21:13,041 --> 02:21:17,712
-Isildur's Bane.
-It has fallen into the hands of the Elves.

1462
02:21:17,879 --> 02:21:21,508
Everyone will try to claim it:
Men, Dwarves, wizards.

1463
02:21:21,675 --> 02:21:25,804
We cannot let that happen.
This thing must come to Gondor.

1464
02:21:27,597 --> 02:21:30,267
-Gondor.
-It's dangerous, I know.

1465
02:21:30,434 --> 02:21:34,146
Ever the Ring will seek to corrupt
the hearts of lesser Men.

1466
02:21:34,312 --> 02:21:38,275
But you, you are strong.
And our need is great.

1467
02:21:38,442 --> 02:21:43,738
It is our blood which is being spilled,
our people who are dying.

1468
02:21:43,905 --> 02:21:48,994
Sauron is biding his time.
He's massing fresh armies.

1469
02:21:49,161 --> 02:21:50,662
He will return.

1470
02:21:50,829 --> 02:21:54,583
And when he does,
we will be powerless to stop him.

1471
02:21:54,749 --> 02:21:57,294
You must go.

1472
02:21:58,462 --> 02:22:00,589
Bring me back this mighty gift.

1473
02:22:01,423 --> 02:22:06,928
No. My place is here with my people.
Not in RivendeII.

1474
02:22:07,095 --> 02:22:10,765
-Would you deny your own father?
-If there is need to go to Rivendell...

1475
02:22:10,932 --> 02:22:13,935
-...send me in his stead.
-You?

1476
02:22:15,103 --> 02:22:17,022
Oh, I see.

1477
02:22:17,189 --> 02:22:21,401
A chance for Faramir, captain of Gender,
to show his quality.

1478
02:22:21,818 --> 02:22:23,820
I think not.

1479
02:22:23,987 --> 02:22:26,865
I trust this mission only to your brother.

1480
02:22:27,032 --> 02:22:29,951
The one who will not fail me.

1481
02:22:47,093 --> 02:22:50,263
Remember today, little brother.

1482
02:23:08,615 --> 02:23:10,617
MAN:
Captain Faramir!

1483
02:23:11,868 --> 02:23:13,995
[WHISPERING]
We found the third one.

1484
02:23:19,584 --> 02:23:21,419
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

1485
02:23:25,507 --> 02:23:27,509
You must come with me. Now.

1486
02:23:38,728 --> 02:23:39,854
Down there.

1487
02:23:54,744 --> 02:23:57,622
To enter the Forbidden Pool
bears the penalty of death.

1488
02:24:08,216 --> 02:24:09,718
They wait for my command.

1489
02:24:15,223 --> 02:24:16,308
Shall I shoot?

1490
02:24:17,559 --> 02:24:20,562
<i>The rock and pool
ls nice and cool</i>

1491
02:24:20,729 --> 02:24:22,564
<i>So juicy sweet</i>

1492
02:24:23,231 --> 02:24:26,192
<i>Our only wish
To catch a fish</i>

1493
02:24:26,359 --> 02:24:29,070
<i>So juicy sweet</i>

1494
02:24:32,532 --> 02:24:34,242
[YELLS]

1495
02:24:36,077 --> 02:24:37,454
Wait.

1496
02:24:38,955 --> 02:24:41,791
This creature is bound to me.

1497
02:24:42,417 --> 02:24:44,336
And I to him.

1498
02:24:47,589 --> 02:24:48,923
He is our guide.

1499
02:24:53,637 --> 02:24:55,055
Please...

1500
02:24:55,221 --> 02:24:57,098
...let me go down to him.

1501
02:25:08,360 --> 02:25:10,028
Sméagol.

1502
02:25:11,029 --> 02:25:13,281
Master is here.

1503
02:25:14,449 --> 02:25:15,617
Come, Sméagol.

1504
02:25:18,453 --> 02:25:21,122
Trust master. Come.

1505
02:25:24,292 --> 02:25:28,129
We must go now?

1506
02:25:28,463 --> 02:25:31,925
Sméagol, you must trust master.

1507
02:25:32,092 --> 02:25:33,468
Follow me. Come on.

1508
02:25:34,678 --> 02:25:36,304
Come.

1509
02:25:38,807 --> 02:25:39,974
Come, Sméagol.

1510
02:25:40,475 --> 02:25:42,560
Nice Sméagol. That's it.

1511
02:25:43,061 --> 02:25:44,604
Come on.

1512
02:25:46,439 --> 02:25:47,691
[FOOTSTEP]

1513
02:25:48,983 --> 02:25:50,652
Don't hurt him!

1514
02:25:50,819 --> 02:25:53,571
Sméagol, don't struggle.
Sméagol, listen to me.

1515
02:25:53,738 --> 02:25:55,031
Master!

1516
02:25:58,118 --> 02:26:00,495
[MUFFLED CRIES]

1517
02:26:06,126 --> 02:26:09,838
[GRUNTING AND PANTING]

1518
02:26:20,223 --> 02:26:22,600
That's enough.

1519
02:26:26,229 --> 02:26:28,398
Where are you leading them?

1520
02:26:28,565 --> 02:26:29,983
[CRYING]

1521
02:26:30,191 --> 02:26:31,860
FARAMIR:
Answer me.

1522
02:26:32,694 --> 02:26:35,905
GOLLUM:
Sméagol.

1523
02:26:36,239 --> 02:26:38,450
[CRYING]

1524
02:26:39,367 --> 02:26:44,122
GOLLUM:
Why does it cry, Sméagol’?

1525
02:26:45,373 --> 02:26:48,001
SMEAGOL:
Cruel Men hurts us.

1526
02:26:48,168 --> 02:26:51,171
Master tricksed us.

1527
02:26:51,337 --> 02:26:54,883
GOLLUM:
Of course he did.

1528
02:26:55,258 --> 02:26:58,970
I told you he was tricksy.

1529
02:26:59,137 --> 02:27:02,182
I told you he was false.

1530
02:27:02,348 --> 02:27:05,059
SMEAGOL:
Master is our friend.

1531
02:27:05,226 --> 02:27:07,562
Our friend.

1532
02:27:07,729 --> 02:27:09,898
GOLLUM:
Master betrayed us.

1533
02:27:10,064 --> 02:27:13,067
SMEAGOL:
No. Not its business.

1534
02:27:14,152 --> 02:27:16,571
Leave us alone!

1535
02:27:16,738 --> 02:27:19,157
GOLLUM:
Filthy little HobbitseS!

1536
02:27:19,324 --> 02:27:21,618
They stole it from us!

1537
02:27:21,785 --> 02:27:23,244
SMEAGOL:
No. No.

1538
02:27:23,787 --> 02:27:25,413
What did they steal?

1539
02:27:27,582 --> 02:27:32,921
GOLLUM:
My precious!

1540
02:27:33,379 --> 02:27:35,924
[YELLS]

1541
02:27:36,591 --> 02:27:38,259
We have to get out of here.

1542
02:27:38,843 --> 02:27:40,804
You go. Go, now.

1543
02:27:43,431 --> 02:27:45,266
You can do it.

1544
02:27:46,726 --> 02:27:48,186
Use the Ring, Mr. Frodo.

1545
02:27:48,353 --> 02:27:50,146
Just this once.

1546
02:27:50,313 --> 02:27:52,106
Put it on.

1547
02:27:52,524 --> 02:27:54,567
Disappear.

1548
02:27:55,610 --> 02:27:56,694
I can't.

1549
02:27:59,781 --> 02:28:01,991
You were right, <i>Sam.</i>

1550
02:28:03,451 --> 02:28:05,954
You tried to tell me but...

1551
02:28:10,625 --> 02:28:12,794
I'm sorry.

1552
02:28:17,340 --> 02:28:20,218
The Ring's taking me, <i>Sam.</i>

1553
02:28:21,636 --> 02:28:23,304
If I put it on...

1554
02:28:23,471 --> 02:28:25,807
...he'll find me.

1555
02:28:27,475 --> 02:28:29,435
He'll see.

1556
02:28:30,645 --> 02:28:32,647
Mr. Frodo....

1557
02:28:37,569 --> 02:28:41,823
So this is the answer
to all the riddles.

1558
02:28:44,033 --> 02:28:47,036
Here in the Wild I have you...

1559
02:28:47,203 --> 02:28:49,122
...two Half lings...

1560
02:28:49,289 --> 02:28:52,458
...and a host of men at my call.

1561
02:28:55,753 --> 02:28:59,257
The Ring of Power within my grasp.

1562
02:29:08,933 --> 02:29:12,687
A chance for Faramir,
captain of Gondor...

1563
02:29:14,272 --> 02:29:17,317
...to show his quality.

1564
02:29:34,834 --> 02:29:37,503
[VOICE OF THE RING WHISPERING]

1565
02:29:38,421 --> 02:29:40,048
No!

1566
02:29:43,217 --> 02:29:44,552
Stop it!

1567
02:29:44,719 --> 02:29:45,762
Leave him alone.

1568
02:29:47,096 --> 02:29:49,599
Don't you understand?

1569
02:29:50,892 --> 02:29:52,810
He's got to destroy it!

1570
02:29:52,977 --> 02:29:56,230
That's where we're going, into Mordor.

1571
02:29:56,397 --> 02:29:58,066
To the Mountain of Fire!

1572
02:29:59,108 --> 02:30:02,236
Osgiliath is under attack.
They call for reinforcements.

1573
02:30:02,403 --> 02:30:05,406
SAM:
Please. It's such a burden.

1574
02:30:07,575 --> 02:30:09,661
Will you not help him?

1575
02:30:10,995 --> 02:30:12,914
Captain?

1576
02:30:13,581 --> 02:30:15,792
Prepare to leave.

1577
02:30:20,755 --> 02:30:23,174
The Ring will go to Gondor.

1578
02:30:33,559 --> 02:30:36,813
[DISTANT MARCHING FOOTSTEPS]

1579
02:31:23,484 --> 02:31:26,571
[SPEAKS IN ELVISH]

1580
02:31:36,164 --> 02:31:38,833
WOMAN: He's alive!
GIMLI: Where is he? Where is he?

1581
02:31:39,000 --> 02:31:42,045
Get out of the way!
I'm going to kill him!

1582
02:31:42,211 --> 02:31:46,007
You are the luckiest, the canniest...

1583
02:31:46,174 --> 02:31:50,178
...and the most reckless man
I ever knew.

1584
02:31:50,845 --> 02:31:52,346
Bless you, laddie.

1585
02:31:52,930 --> 02:31:54,682
Gimli, where is the king?

1586
02:32:03,691 --> 02:32:04,734
[IN ELVISH]
You're late.

1587
02:32:08,446 --> 02:32:09,781
[IN ENGLISH]
You look terrible.

1588
02:32:36,849 --> 02:32:39,685
[SPEAKS IN ELVISH]

1589
02:32:45,149 --> 02:32:46,192
[DOORS OPENING]

1590
02:32:51,531 --> 02:32:53,574
A great host, you say?

1591
02:32:53,741 --> 02:32:55,201
[IN ENGLISH]
All Isengard is emptied.

1592
02:32:55,368 --> 02:32:56,410
How many?

1593
02:32:57,078 --> 02:33:00,081
ARAGORN:
Ten thousand strong at least.

1594
02:33:01,624 --> 02:33:03,084
Ten thousand?

1595
02:33:03,501 --> 02:33:06,003
It is an army bred for a single purpose:

1596
02:33:08,673 --> 02:33:10,800
To destroy the world of Men.

1597
02:33:13,302 --> 02:33:15,304
They will be here by nightfall.

1598
02:33:21,144 --> 02:33:22,436
Let them come!

1599
02:33:23,938 --> 02:33:26,732
I want every man and strong lad
able to bear arms...

1600
02:33:26,899 --> 02:33:30,027
...to be ready for battle by nightfall.

1601
02:33:38,286 --> 02:33:41,205
We will cover the causeway
and the gate from above.

1602
02:33:41,372 --> 02:33:43,791
No army has ever breached
the Deeping Wall...

1603
02:33:43,958 --> 02:33:46,711
...or set foot inside the Hornburg!

1604
02:33:46,878 --> 02:33:49,297
This is no rabble of mindless Orcs.

1605
02:33:49,881 --> 02:33:52,091
These are Uruk-hai.

1606
02:33:52,258 --> 02:33:55,678
Their armour is thick
and their shields broad.

1607
02:33:57,305 --> 02:34:00,975
I have fought many wars,
Master Dwarf.

1608
02:34:01,142 --> 02:34:04,770
I know how to defend my own keep.

1609
02:34:11,360 --> 02:34:14,780
They will break upon this fortress
like water on rock.

1610
02:34:14,947 --> 02:34:20,161
Saruman's hordes will pillage and burn.
We've seen it before.

1611
02:34:20,369 --> 02:34:23,039
Crops can be resown...

1612
02:34:23,206 --> 02:34:26,209
...homes rebuilt.

1613
02:34:26,834 --> 02:34:29,378
Within these walls...

1614
02:34:29,754 --> 02:34:31,255
...we will outlast them.

1615
02:34:31,422 --> 02:34:33,841
They do not come to destroy Rohan's
crops or villages.

1616
02:34:34,008 --> 02:34:35,551
They come to destroy its people...

1617
02:34:35,718 --> 02:34:38,221
...down to the last child.

1618
02:34:39,096 --> 02:34:41,349
What would you have me do?

1619
02:34:41,515 --> 02:34:43,267
Look at my men.

1620
02:34:43,434 --> 02:34:45,186
Their courage hangs by a thread.

1621
02:34:47,355 --> 02:34:51,776
If this is to be our end, then I would
have them make such an end...

1622
02:34:51,943 --> 02:34:54,987
...as to be worthy of remembrance.

1623
02:34:58,616 --> 02:35:00,534
ARAGORN:
Send out riders, my lord.

1624
02:35:00,826 --> 02:35:03,704
You must call for aid.

1625
02:35:06,958 --> 02:35:09,210
And who will come?

1626
02:35:09,627 --> 02:35:11,212
Elves?

1627
02:35:11,379 --> 02:35:13,464
Dwarves?

1628
02:35:14,215 --> 02:35:17,093
We are not so lucky in our friends
as you.

1629
02:35:17,927 --> 02:35:20,221
The old alliances are dead.

1630
02:35:20,638 --> 02:35:23,432
-Gondor will answer.
-Gondor?!

1631
02:35:23,599 --> 02:35:25,810
Where was Gondor
when the Westfold fell?!

1632
02:35:26,769 --> 02:35:30,022
Where was Gondor when
our enemies closed in around us?!

1633
02:35:30,189 --> 02:35:32,108
Where was Gon--’?

1634
02:35:34,777 --> 02:35:36,737
No, my Lord Aragorn...

1635
02:35:38,322 --> 02:35:40,783
...we are alone.

1636
02:35:47,665 --> 02:35:49,417
Get the women and children
into the caves.

1637
02:35:49,583 --> 02:35:50,835
MAN 1: We need more time
to lay provisions--

1638
02:35:51,002 --> 02:35:54,505
THEODEN:
There is no time. War is upon us.

1639
02:35:54,755 --> 02:35:56,465
MAN 2:
Secure the gate.

1640
02:35:57,133 --> 02:36:00,052
[CAWING]

1641
02:36:01,679 --> 02:36:03,764
We Ents have not troubled...

1642
02:36:03,973 --> 02:36:07,351
...about the wars of Men and wizards...

1643
02:36:08,102 --> 02:36:11,105
...for a very long time.

1644
02:36:12,356 --> 02:36:17,111
But now, something
is about to happen...

1645
02:36:17,278 --> 02:36:19,613
...that has not happened...

1646
02:36:19,822 --> 02:36:22,283
...for an age.

1647
02:36:23,492 --> 02:36:25,786
Entmoot.

1648
02:36:26,162 --> 02:36:27,204
What's that?

1649
02:36:27,621 --> 02:36:30,458
'Tis a gathering.

1650
02:36:31,625 --> 02:36:34,211
A gathering of what?

1651
02:36:34,503 --> 02:36:37,548
[RUMBLING]

1652
02:36:52,146 --> 02:36:54,482
TREEBEARD:
Beech. Oak.

1653
02:36:54,648 --> 02:36:56,567
Chestnut. Ash.

1654
02:36:56,817 --> 02:36:58,819
Good. Good. Good.

1655
02:36:58,986 --> 02:37:01,322
Many have come.

1656
02:37:08,871 --> 02:37:11,665
Now we must decide
if the Ents...

1657
02:37:11,832 --> 02:37:14,377
...will go to war.

1658
02:37:23,344 --> 02:37:26,389
GUARD 1:
Move back! Move to the caves!

1659
02:37:28,849 --> 02:37:30,935
GUARD 2:
Come on, people! Quickly, now!

1660
02:37:31,352 --> 02:37:33,646
We'll place the reserves along the wall.

1661
02:37:33,813 --> 02:37:36,107
They can support the archers
from above the gate.

1662
02:37:36,273 --> 02:37:39,402
Aragorn, you must rest.

1663
02:37:39,568 --> 02:37:41,070
You're no use to us half alive.

1664
02:37:41,237 --> 02:37:42,279
[BABY CRYING]

1665
02:37:42,446 --> 02:37:43,656
EOWYN:
Aragorn!

1666
02:37:47,034 --> 02:37:50,079
I'm to be sent with the women
into the caves.

1667
02:37:50,246 --> 02:37:51,914
That is an honorable charge.

1668
02:37:52,081 --> 02:37:54,959
To mind the children, to find food
and bedding when the men return.

1669
02:37:55,126 --> 02:37:56,836
What renown is there in that?

1670
02:37:57,002 --> 02:38:00,714
My lady, a time may come for valor
without renown.

1671
02:38:00,965 --> 02:38:03,759
Who then will your people look to
in the last defense?

1672
02:38:03,926 --> 02:38:08,931
-Let me stand at your side.
-It is not in my power to command it.

1673
02:38:09,223 --> 02:38:12,059
You do not command
the others to stay!

1674
02:38:12,226 --> 02:38:15,980
They fight beside you because they
would not be parted from you.

1675
02:38:17,148 --> 02:38:19,358
Because they love you.

1676
02:38:26,449 --> 02:38:27,992
I'm sorry.

1677
02:38:39,462 --> 02:38:41,338
[BABY CRYING]

1678
02:39:04,904 --> 02:39:07,865
[MUTED SPEECH]

1679
02:39:23,422 --> 02:39:26,800
[CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

1680
02:39:33,891 --> 02:39:37,186
Farmers, farriers, stable boys.

1681
02:39:38,270 --> 02:39:40,064
These are no soldiers.

1682
02:39:42,316 --> 02:39:45,819
-Most have seen too many winters.
-Or too few.

1683
02:39:49,740 --> 02:39:52,660
Look at them. They're frightened.

1684
02:39:52,826 --> 02:39:54,286
I can see it in their eyes.

1685
02:39:59,500 --> 02:40:01,502
[IN ELVISH]
And they should be...

1686
02:40:01,669 --> 02:40:04,797
Three hundred... against ten thousand!

1687
02:40:06,507 --> 02:40:08,592
[IN ELVISH] They have more hope of
defending themselves here than at Edoras...

1688
02:40:08,759 --> 02:40:10,010
Aragorn.

1689
02:40:10,177 --> 02:40:12,846
They cannot win this fight.

1690
02:40:13,764 --> 02:40:15,057
They are all going to die!

1691
02:40:15,224 --> 02:40:17,434
[IN ENGLISH]
Then I shall die as one of them!

1692
02:40:23,857 --> 02:40:25,693
GIMLI:
Let him go, lad.

1693
02:40:26,277 --> 02:40:28,195
Let him be.

1694
02:40:29,697 --> 02:40:35,202
Every villager able to wield a sword
has been sent to the armoury.

1695
02:40:39,456 --> 02:40:41,375
My lord?

1696
02:40:43,419 --> 02:40:46,005
Who am I, Gamling?

1697
02:40:49,383 --> 02:40:53,262
You are our king, sire.

1698
02:40:56,265 --> 02:40:59,560
And do you trust your king?

1699
02:41:01,061 --> 02:41:04,231
Your men, my lord...

1700
02:41:04,398 --> 02:41:07,234
...will follow you to whatever end.

1701
02:41:14,074 --> 02:41:15,993
To whatever end.

1702
02:41:25,836 --> 02:41:29,423
Where is the horse and the rider?

1703
02:41:29,590 --> 02:41:32,635
Where is the horn that was blowing?

1704
02:41:34,136 --> 02:41:38,599
<i>They have passed like rain
on the mountains.</i>

1705
02:41:39,600 --> 02:41:42,811
<i>Like wind in the meadow.</i>

1706
02:41:46,482 --> 02:41:50,277
The days have gone down in the West...

1707
02:41:50,944 --> 02:41:53,614
<i>...behind the hills...</i>

1708
02:41:55,491 --> 02:41:57,117
<i>...into Shadow.</i>

1709
02:42:05,584 --> 02:42:09,004
How did it come to this?

1710
02:42:18,597 --> 02:42:21,433
[ENTS GROANING]

1711
02:42:25,312 --> 02:42:26,939
Huh?

1712
02:42:30,317 --> 02:42:32,152
It's been going for hours.

1713
02:42:33,320 --> 02:42:35,739
They must have decided something
by now.

1714
02:42:35,906 --> 02:42:39,993
TREEBEARD:
Decided? No.

1715
02:42:40,160 --> 02:42:45,332
We only just finished saying...

1716
02:42:46,500 --> 02:42:48,377
...good morning.

1717
02:42:49,712 --> 02:42:52,923
But it's nighttime already.

1718
02:42:53,090 --> 02:42:54,883
You can't take forever.

1719
02:42:55,884 --> 02:42:57,970
Don't be hasty.

1720
02:42:58,387 --> 02:43:00,806
We're running out of time!

1721
02:43:03,851 --> 02:43:06,770
GUARD:
Move! Move to the outer wall.

1722
02:43:24,329 --> 02:43:25,664
Give me your sword.

1723
02:43:35,132 --> 02:43:36,341
What is your name?

1724
02:43:36,884 --> 02:43:39,219
Haleth, son of Héma, my lord.

1725
02:43:41,388 --> 02:43:44,016
The men are saying that
we will not live out the night.

1726
02:43:45,976 --> 02:43:47,936
They say that it is hopeless.

1727
02:44:05,746 --> 02:44:07,414
This is a good sword.

1728
02:44:09,416 --> 02:44:11,752
Haleth, son of Héma...

1729
02:44:16,089 --> 02:44:18,258
...there is always hope.

1730
02:44:41,240 --> 02:44:44,618
We have trusted you this far.
You have not led us astray.

1731
02:44:44,785 --> 02:44:46,328
Forgive me.

1732
02:44:46,495 --> 02:44:47,955
I was wrong to despair.

1733
02:44:51,124 --> 02:44:53,627
[IN ELVISH]
There is nothing to forgive, Legolas.

1734
02:44:56,797 --> 02:44:59,967
We had time, I'd get this adjusted.

1735
02:45:03,387 --> 02:45:05,472
It's a little tight across the chest.

1736
02:45:08,100 --> 02:45:10,352
[HORN BLOWING]

1737
02:45:11,645 --> 02:45:13,605
That is no Orc horn.

1738
02:45:19,278 --> 02:45:21,113
Send for the king.

1739
02:45:21,280 --> 02:45:24,867
-Open the gate!
GUARD: Open up the gate!

1740
02:45:56,523 --> 02:45:58,191
How is this possible?

1741
02:45:59,192 --> 02:46:02,863
I bring word from Elrond of Rivendell.

1742
02:46:03,030 --> 02:46:06,241
An alliance once existed
between Elves and Men.

1743
02:46:06,950 --> 02:46:11,204
Long ago we fought and died together.

1744
02:46:13,457 --> 02:46:16,376
We come to honor that allegiance.

1745
02:46:16,793 --> 02:46:19,046
[SPEAKING IN ELVISH]

1746
02:46:24,843 --> 02:46:26,762
[IN ENGLISH]
You are most welcome.

1747
02:46:32,142 --> 02:46:35,938
We are proud to fight
alongside Men once more.

1748
02:46:58,210 --> 02:47:02,089
[MARCHING FOOTSTEPS
APPROACHING]

1749
02:47:02,422 --> 02:47:05,759
[INDISTINCT GRUNTING
AND GROWLING]

1750
02:47:09,721 --> 02:47:12,975
GIMLI:
You could have picked a better spot.

1751
02:47:17,813 --> 02:47:22,025
Well, lad, whatever luck you live by,
let's hope it lasts the night.

1752
02:47:23,235 --> 02:47:25,195
[THUNDER ROLLS]

1753
02:47:28,156 --> 02:47:29,950
Your friends are with you, Aragorn.

1754
02:47:30,575 --> 02:47:33,078
Let's hope they last the night.

1755
02:47:36,039 --> 02:47:38,917
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

1756
02:48:08,030 --> 02:48:11,074
[MARCHING FOOTSTEPS
APPROACHING]

1757
02:48:15,620 --> 02:48:17,289
[BABY CRYING]

1758
02:48:33,055 --> 02:48:36,808
[IN ELVISH]
Show them no mercy...

1759
02:48:37,809 --> 02:48:40,103
for you shall receive none!

1760
02:48:44,316 --> 02:48:46,610
[ROARS]

1761
02:49:14,513 --> 02:49:17,349
-What's happening out there?
-Shall I describe it to you?

1762
02:49:18,600 --> 02:49:20,393
Or would you like me to find you a box?

1763
02:49:23,438 --> 02:49:27,859
[U RU K-HAI BATTLE CRIES]

1764
02:49:59,891 --> 02:50:01,101
HOLD!

1765
02:50:03,145 --> 02:50:05,147
[GROANS]

1766
02:50:23,582 --> 02:50:25,417
So it begins.

1767
02:50:31,298 --> 02:50:32,465
Prepare to fire!

1768
02:50:41,474 --> 02:50:43,685
[IN ELVISH]
Their armour is weak at the neck...

1769
02:50:43,852 --> 02:50:45,353
and beneath the arm.

1770
02:50:45,562 --> 02:50:47,314
Release Arrows!

1771
02:50:52,277 --> 02:50:53,612
Did they hit anything?

1772
02:50:54,279 --> 02:50:56,281
Give them a volley.

1773
02:50:56,448 --> 02:50:58,575
-Fire!
-Fire!

1774
02:51:03,955 --> 02:51:07,417
[SPEAKS IN ELVISH]

1775
02:51:14,299 --> 02:51:15,967
Send them to me! Come on!

1776
02:51:35,528 --> 02:51:36,571
Ladders!

1777
02:51:36,780 --> 02:51:37,822
Good!

1778
02:51:44,621 --> 02:51:47,624
[IN ENGLISH]
Swords! Swords!

1779
02:52:25,704 --> 02:52:27,831
Legolas! Two already!

1780
02:52:27,998 --> 02:52:30,125
[IN ENGLISH]
I'm on 17!

1781
02:52:30,292 --> 02:52:32,877
I'll have no pointy-ear outscoring me!

1782
02:52:39,676 --> 02:52:41,386
Nineteen!

1783
02:53:02,949 --> 02:53:05,994
[ENTS GROANING]

1784
02:53:07,370 --> 02:53:08,788
Merry.

1785
02:53:13,209 --> 02:53:17,005
We have just agreed.

1786
02:53:27,015 --> 02:53:28,475
Yes?

1787
02:53:29,976 --> 02:53:34,147
I have told your names to the Entmoot...

1788
02:53:35,273 --> 02:53:38,526
...and we have agreed...

1789
02:53:38,985 --> 02:53:43,031
...you are not Orcs.

1790
02:53:44,783 --> 02:53:46,910
Well, that's good news.

1791
02:53:47,077 --> 02:53:51,206
And what about Saruman?
Have you come to a decision about him?

1792
02:53:51,831 --> 02:53:55,627
Now, don't be hasty, Master Meriadoc.

1793
02:53:55,794 --> 02:53:57,337
Hasty?

1794
02:53:58,129 --> 02:54:00,006
Our friends are out there.

1795
02:54:00,173 --> 02:54:04,344
They need our help. They cannot
fight this war on their own.

1796
02:54:04,677 --> 02:54:06,971
War? Yes.

1797
02:54:07,138 --> 02:54:09,015
It affects us all.

1798
02:54:09,182 --> 02:54:12,185
Tree, root and twig.

1799
02:54:13,061 --> 02:54:17,107
But you must understand, young Hobbit...

1800
02:54:17,315 --> 02:54:19,234
...it takes a long time...

1801
02:54:19,401 --> 02:54:24,322
...to say anything in Old Entish...

1802
02:54:24,489 --> 02:54:28,701
...and we never say anything...

1803
02:54:28,868 --> 02:54:32,789
...unless it is worth taking...

1804
02:54:32,956 --> 02:54:37,001
...a long time to say.

1805
02:54:37,794 --> 02:54:41,089
Seventeen! Eighteen!

1806
02:54:41,256 --> 02:54:42,340
Nineteen!

1807
02:54:42,882 --> 02:54:44,759
Twenty!

1808
02:54:44,926 --> 02:54:46,594
Twenty-one!

1809
02:54:56,688 --> 02:54:57,730
Causeway!

1810
02:54:57,897 --> 02:54:59,899
[ARAGORN SHOUTS IN ELVISH]

1811
02:55:06,448 --> 02:55:08,825
Is this it?

1812
02:55:08,992 --> 02:55:11,911
Is this all you can conjure, Saruman?

1813
02:55:38,313 --> 02:55:39,689
[IN ELVISH]
Bring him down, Legolas!

1814
02:55:43,026 --> 02:55:43,860
Kill him!

1815
02:55:44,027 --> 02:55:45,069
Kill him!

1816
02:56:37,914 --> 02:56:39,290
Brace the gate!

1817
02:56:57,600 --> 02:56:59,852
Hold them! Stand firm!

1818
02:57:07,735 --> 02:57:09,070
Aragorn!

1819
02:57:13,700 --> 02:57:14,909
Gimli!

1820
02:57:21,165 --> 02:57:22,625
[SPEAKS IN ELVISH]

1821
02:57:25,503 --> 02:57:26,588
[IN ELVISH]
Charge!

1822
02:58:03,666 --> 02:58:07,587
The Ents cannot hold back this storm.

1823
02:58:08,379 --> 02:58:12,383
We must weather such things
as we have always done.

1824
02:58:13,217 --> 02:58:15,303
How can that be your decision?!

1825
02:58:15,970 --> 02:58:19,599
This is not our war.

1826
02:58:19,891 --> 02:58:22,101
But you're part of this world!

1827
02:58:26,230 --> 02:58:28,066
Aren't you?!

1828
02:58:29,025 --> 02:58:31,736
[ENTS GRUMBLING]

1829
02:58:32,153 --> 02:58:34,530
You must help. Please.

1830
02:58:35,823 --> 02:58:38,576
You must do something.

1831
02:58:38,868 --> 02:58:43,164
You are young and brave, Master Merry.

1832
02:58:44,374 --> 02:58:48,086
But your part in this tale is over.

1833
02:58:48,252 --> 02:58:50,505
Go back to your home.

1834
02:59:00,515 --> 02:59:02,767
Maybe Treebeard's right.

1835
02:59:02,934 --> 02:59:04,811
We don't belong here, Merry.

1836
02:59:04,977 --> 02:59:07,271
It's too big for us.

1837
02:59:07,438 --> 02:59:10,108
What can we do in the end?

1838
02:59:12,402 --> 02:59:15,029
We've got the Shire.

1839
02:59:15,571 --> 02:59:18,116
Maybe we should go home.

1840
02:59:19,951 --> 02:59:23,162
The fires of Isengard will spread...

1841
02:59:23,329 --> 02:59:28,251
...and the woods of Tuckborough
and Buckland will burn.

1842
02:59:28,418 --> 02:59:30,002
And....

1843
02:59:31,796 --> 02:59:34,882
And all that was once green and good
in this world will be gone.

1844
02:59:38,428 --> 02:59:41,347
There won't be a Shire, Pippin.

1845
03:00:00,867 --> 03:00:02,118
GAMLING:
Aragorn!

1846
03:00:02,285 --> 03:00:04,662
Fall back to the Keep!

1847
03:00:04,829 --> 03:00:07,915
Get your men out of there!

1848
03:00:09,041 --> 03:00:10,543
[IN ELVISH]
To the Keep!

1849
03:00:15,381 --> 03:00:17,008
Pull back to the Keep!

1850
03:00:17,550 --> 03:00:19,218
Haldir!

1851
03:00:20,011 --> 03:00:21,471
To the Keep!

1852
03:00:23,347 --> 03:00:26,601
GIMLI: What are you doing?
What are you stopping for?

1853
03:00:26,851 --> 03:00:29,020
[SHOUTING IN ELVISH]

1854
03:00:45,828 --> 03:00:47,038
Haldir!

1855
03:01:29,747 --> 03:01:31,249
MAN:
Brace the gate!

1856
03:01:33,459 --> 03:01:34,752
Hold them!

1857
03:01:36,587 --> 03:01:39,966
To the gate. Draw your swords!

1858
03:02:08,119 --> 03:02:10,037
Make way!

1859
03:02:12,957 --> 03:02:14,667
We cannot hold much longer!

1860
03:02:20,631 --> 03:02:24,218
THEODEN: Hold them!
-How long do you need?

1861
03:02:24,385 --> 03:02:26,971
As long as you can give me.

1862
03:02:27,138 --> 03:02:28,806
Gimli!

1863
03:02:30,266 --> 03:02:31,642
Timbers!

1864
03:02:31,809 --> 03:02:33,769
MAN:
Brace the gate!

1865
03:02:48,534 --> 03:02:50,244
Come on. We can take them.

1866
03:02:51,078 --> 03:02:52,705
It's a long way.

1867
03:02:57,960 --> 03:02:59,712
Toss me.

1868
03:03:00,880 --> 03:03:02,715
-What?
-I cannot jump the distance!

1869
03:03:02,882 --> 03:03:04,467
You'll have to toss me!

1870
03:03:10,056 --> 03:03:11,349
Don't tell the Elf.

1871
03:03:11,849 --> 03:03:13,643
Not a word.

1872
03:03:28,866 --> 03:03:30,326
Shore up the door!

1873
03:03:30,493 --> 03:03:32,578
MAN 1: Make way!
MAN 2: Follow me to the barricade.

1874
03:03:32,745 --> 03:03:33,829
MAN 1:
Watch our backs!

1875
03:03:37,959 --> 03:03:40,211
MAN 3: Throw another one over here!
-Higher!

1876
03:04:30,136 --> 03:04:31,554
MAN 4:
Hold fast the gate!

1877
03:04:35,766 --> 03:04:38,728
Gimli! Aragorn!
Get out of there!

1878
03:04:43,441 --> 03:04:45,067
Aragorn!

1879
03:05:18,476 --> 03:05:20,936
Pull everybody back.

1880
03:05:21,312 --> 03:05:23,105
Pull them back.

1881
03:05:23,647 --> 03:05:25,107
Fall back!

1882
03:05:25,274 --> 03:05:27,777
Fall back!

1883
03:05:28,944 --> 03:05:30,529
THEODEN:
They have broken through!

1884
03:05:30,696 --> 03:05:33,074
The castle is breached. Retreat!

1885
03:05:33,240 --> 03:05:35,493
GAMLING: Fall back!
THEODEN: Retreat!

1886
03:05:35,659 --> 03:05:38,245
ARAGORN:
Hurry! Inside. Get them inside!

1887
03:05:38,412 --> 03:05:40,664
THEODEN:
Into the Keep!

1888
03:05:52,134 --> 03:05:57,098
I will leave you at the western borders
of the forest.

1889
03:05:57,264 --> 03:06:01,977
You can make your way north
to your homeland from there.

1890
03:06:07,691 --> 03:06:08,984
Wait! Stop!

1891
03:06:09,860 --> 03:06:11,362
Stop!

1892
03:06:14,490 --> 03:06:16,200
Turn around.

1893
03:06:17,118 --> 03:06:19,829
-Turn around. Take us south.
-South?

1894
03:06:19,995 --> 03:06:25,000
But that will lead you past Isengard.

1895
03:06:25,334 --> 03:06:28,045
Yes. Exactly.

1896
03:06:28,212 --> 03:06:31,423
If we go south, we can slip
past Saruman unnoticed.

1897
03:06:31,590 --> 03:06:34,260
The closer we are to danger,
the farther we are from harm.

1898
03:06:34,426 --> 03:06:36,428
It's the last thing he'll expect.

1899
03:06:39,056 --> 03:06:42,059
That doesn't make sense to me.

1900
03:06:42,226 --> 03:06:43,394
But then...

1901
03:06:43,561 --> 03:06:46,272
...you are very small.

1902
03:06:46,730 --> 03:06:48,524
Perhaps you're right.

1903
03:06:51,152 --> 03:06:52,695
South it is, then.

1904
03:06:54,196 --> 03:06:57,533
Hold on, little Shirelings.

1905
03:06:59,577 --> 03:07:02,329
I always like going south.

1906
03:07:02,496 --> 03:07:06,792
Somehow it feels like going downhill.

1907
03:07:07,418 --> 03:07:09,879
Are you mad? We'll be caught.

1908
03:07:10,045 --> 03:07:11,964
No, we won't.

1909
03:07:12,715 --> 03:07:14,967
Not this time.

1910
03:07:21,599 --> 03:07:22,641
MAN:
Look!

1911
03:07:24,268 --> 03:07:26,729
Osgiliath burns!

1912
03:07:26,896 --> 03:07:28,314
Mordor has come.

1913
03:07:29,440 --> 03:07:31,859
The Ring will not save Gondor.

1914
03:07:33,194 --> 03:07:35,404
It has only the power to destroy.

1915
03:07:36,280 --> 03:07:37,740
Please...

1916
03:07:37,907 --> 03:07:39,533
...let me go.

1917
03:07:40,576 --> 03:07:42,161
Hurry.

1918
03:07:45,623 --> 03:07:47,041
FRODO:
Faramir!

1919
03:07:47,208 --> 03:07:49,543
You must let me go!

1920
03:07:50,127 --> 03:07:53,589
TREEBEARD:
And those little family of field mice...

1921
03:07:53,756 --> 03:07:56,592
...that climb up sometimes,
and they tickle me awfully.

1922
03:07:57,301 --> 03:08:00,638
They're always trying to get somewhere
where they....

1923
03:08:01,055 --> 03:08:03,390
[GASPS]

1924
03:08:11,815 --> 03:08:14,735
Many of these trees were my friends.

1925
03:08:15,444 --> 03:08:20,074
Creatures I had known
from nut and acorn.

1926
03:08:21,242 --> 03:08:22,451
I'm sorry, Treebeard.

1927
03:08:22,618 --> 03:08:25,371
They had voices of their own.

1928
03:08:27,623 --> 03:08:30,167
Saruman.

1929
03:08:30,501 --> 03:08:33,587
A wizard should know better!

1930
03:08:36,006 --> 03:08:38,926
[ROARING]

1931
03:08:47,851 --> 03:08:51,522
There is no curse in Elvish...

1932
03:08:51,689 --> 03:08:54,358
...Entish or the tongues of Men...

1933
03:08:54,525 --> 03:08:56,860
...for this treachery.

1934
03:08:58,279 --> 03:09:01,115
Look! The trees! They're moving!

1935
03:09:05,828 --> 03:09:07,037
Where are they going?

1936
03:09:07,538 --> 03:09:10,791
They have business with the Orcs.

1937
03:09:11,250 --> 03:09:15,546
My business is with Isengard tonight...

1938
03:09:15,713 --> 03:09:18,340
...with rock and stone.

1939
03:09:18,716 --> 03:09:22,636
[GROANING AND FOOTSTEPS
APPROACHING]

1940
03:09:42,239 --> 03:09:43,407
Yes.

1941
03:09:44,491 --> 03:09:45,909
TREEBEARD:
Come, my friends.

1942
03:09:47,244 --> 03:09:51,457
The Ents are going to war.

1943
03:09:51,623 --> 03:09:53,417
It is likely...

1944
03:09:53,584 --> 03:09:57,087
...that we go to our doom.

1945
03:09:58,505 --> 03:10:00,966
Last march...

1946
03:10:01,508 --> 03:10:03,552
<i>...oi the Ems.</i>

1947
03:10:51,642 --> 03:10:55,396
Faramir! Orcs have taken the eastern
shore. Their numbers are too great.

1948
03:10:55,562 --> 03:10:57,648
By nightfall we will be overrun.

1949
03:11:00,401 --> 03:11:01,860
Mr. Frodo?

1950
03:11:02,152 --> 03:11:06,281
It's calling to him, Sam.
His Eye is almost on me.

1951
03:11:06,448 --> 03:11:08,951
Hold on, Mr. Frodo.
You'll be all right.

1952
03:11:11,453 --> 03:11:14,331
[MUTED SPEECH]

1953
03:11:23,257 --> 03:11:24,675
Take them to my father.

1954
03:11:26,218 --> 03:11:29,221
Tell him Faramir sends a mighty gift.

1955
03:11:31,640 --> 03:11:34,685
A weapon that will change our fortunes
in this war.

1956
03:11:35,853 --> 03:11:38,522
Do you want to know
what happened to Boromir?

1957
03:11:39,189 --> 03:11:41,942
You want to know
why your brother died?

1958
03:11:42,443 --> 03:11:46,196
He tried to take the Ring from Frodo
after swearing an oath to protect him!

1959
03:11:46,363 --> 03:11:48,240
He tried to kill him!

1960
03:11:48,407 --> 03:11:50,742
The Ring drove your brother mad!

1961
03:11:51,535 --> 03:11:53,370
ITHILIEN RANGER:
Watch out!

1962
03:12:01,044 --> 03:12:04,006
[RUMBLING]

1963
03:12:04,298 --> 03:12:05,424
Mr. Frodo?

1964
03:12:08,051 --> 03:12:09,887
They're here.

1965
03:12:13,015 --> 03:12:15,476
They've come.

1966
03:12:16,101 --> 03:12:17,728
[RINGWRAITH SCREECHING]

1967
03:12:18,061 --> 03:12:19,938
NangI!

1968
03:12:20,147 --> 03:12:22,441
[ROARING]

1969
03:12:42,085 --> 03:12:44,254
Stay here. Keep out of sight.

1970
03:12:46,048 --> 03:12:48,258
Take cover!

1971
03:13:05,609 --> 03:13:07,152
THEODEN:
The fortress is taken.

1972
03:13:07,945 --> 03:13:09,112
It is over.

1973
03:13:09,279 --> 03:13:13,242
You said this fortress would never fall
while your men defend it.

1974
03:13:13,408 --> 03:13:16,328
They still defend it.
They have died defending it.

1975
03:13:19,081 --> 03:13:20,457
WOMAN 1:
They're breaking in!

1976
03:13:23,126 --> 03:13:25,629
WOMAN 2:
They're past the door!

1977
03:13:28,966 --> 03:13:33,095
Is there no other way for the women
and children to get out of the caves?

1978
03:13:35,764 --> 03:13:37,683
Is there no other way?

1979
03:13:39,268 --> 03:13:42,312
There is one passage.
It leads into the mountains.

1980
03:13:42,980 --> 03:13:45,190
But they will not get far.
The Uruk-hai are too many.

1981
03:13:50,070 --> 03:13:52,489
Tell the women and children
to make for the mountain pass.

1982
03:13:52,656 --> 03:13:55,492
-And barricade the entrance!
-So much death.

1983
03:13:57,661 --> 03:14:01,081
What can Men do
against such reckless hate?

1984
03:14:05,752 --> 03:14:07,170
Ride out with me.

1985
03:14:11,300 --> 03:14:12,926
Ride out and meet them.

1986
03:14:13,677 --> 03:14:15,846
For death and glory.

1987
03:14:16,013 --> 03:14:17,431
For Rohan.

1988
03:14:18,932 --> 03:14:20,392
For your people.

1989
03:14:21,143 --> 03:14:23,061
The sun is rising.

1990
03:14:27,566 --> 03:14:30,569
<i>GANDALF: Look to my coming
at first light on the fifth day.</i>

1991
03:14:30,736 --> 03:14:32,154
<i>At dawn...</i>

1992
03:14:32,321 --> 03:14:34,031
<i>...look to the east.</i>

1993
03:14:38,201 --> 03:14:39,870
Yes.

1994
03:14:42,331 --> 03:14:43,999
Yes.

1995
03:14:45,334 --> 03:14:47,711
The horn of Helm Hammerhand...

1996
03:14:47,878 --> 03:14:50,714
...shall sound in the Deep...

1997
03:14:51,131 --> 03:14:53,133
...one last time.

1998
03:14:53,300 --> 03:14:54,801
Yes!

1999
03:14:57,846 --> 03:15:01,642
Let this be the hour
when we draw swords together.

2000
03:15:09,399 --> 03:15:10,734
Fell deeds, awake.

2001
03:15:11,943 --> 03:15:13,070
Now for wrath...

2002
03:15:13,236 --> 03:15:16,615
...now for ruin and a red dawn.

2003
03:15:17,240 --> 03:15:20,285
[HORN BLOWS]

2004
03:15:23,664 --> 03:15:25,916
Forth Eorlingas!

2005
03:15:26,208 --> 03:15:28,585
[BATTLE CRIES]

2006
03:16:09,084 --> 03:16:10,961
[HORSE NEIGHS]

2007
03:16:13,714 --> 03:16:14,965
Gandalf.

2008
03:16:22,222 --> 03:16:25,892
Théoden King stands alone.

2009
03:16:26,476 --> 03:16:28,645
Not alone.

2010
03:16:29,062 --> 03:16:30,188
Rohirrim!

2011
03:16:36,111 --> 03:16:37,279
Eomer.

2012
03:16:37,446 --> 03:16:39,990
To the king!

2013
03:17:57,567 --> 03:17:59,361
Yes!

2014
03:17:59,903 --> 03:18:01,112
[GRUNTS]

2015
03:18:03,073 --> 03:18:05,408
[ENTS ROARING]

2016
03:18:08,495 --> 03:18:11,790
TREEBEARD:
A hit. A fine hit.

2017
03:18:11,957 --> 03:18:12,999
[TREEBEARD GRUNTS]

2018
03:18:36,481 --> 03:18:38,942
TREEBEARD:
Break the dam!

2019
03:18:39,109 --> 03:18:42,571
Release the river!

2020
03:19:09,890 --> 03:19:12,642
Pippin! Hold on!

2021
03:19:17,898 --> 03:19:20,817
Hold on, little Hobbits.

2022
03:20:02,192 --> 03:20:04,194
What are you doing?

2023
03:20:12,786 --> 03:20:14,371
Where are you going?

2024
03:20:15,538 --> 03:20:19,751
[RUMBLING]

2025
03:20:52,826 --> 03:20:54,786
[ROARING]

2026
03:21:03,878 --> 03:21:05,130
[YELLS]

2027
03:21:12,512 --> 03:21:13,847
It's me.

2028
03:21:16,349 --> 03:21:18,560
It's your <i>Sam.</i>

2029
03:21:22,897 --> 03:21:25,525
Don't you know your Sam?

2030
03:21:33,950 --> 03:21:35,368
[PANTING]

2031
03:21:35,535 --> 03:21:37,078
[SWORD CLANGS]

2032
03:21:43,251 --> 03:21:46,629
I can't do this, <i>Sam.</i>

2033
03:21:47,505 --> 03:21:49,507
I know.

2034
03:21:50,508 --> 03:21:52,886
It's all wrong.

2035
03:21:53,636 --> 03:21:55,638
By rights, we shouldn't even be here.

2036
03:22:03,063 --> 03:22:05,148
But we are.

2037
03:22:11,571 --> 03:22:14,616
It's like in the great stories, Mr. Frodo.

2038
03:22:14,783 --> 03:22:17,160
The ones that really mattered.

2039
03:22:18,203 --> 03:22:21,206
Full of darkness and danger they were.

2040
03:22:21,372 --> 03:22:24,334
And sometimes you didn't want
to know the end...

2041
03:22:24,501 --> 03:22:27,462
...because how could the end be happy?

2042
03:22:30,006 --> 03:22:32,217
<i>How could the world go back
to the way it was...</i>

2043
03:22:32,383 --> 03:22:35,887
<i>...when so much bad had happened?</i>

2044
03:22:36,721 --> 03:22:38,640
Victory!

2045
03:22:38,807 --> 03:22:40,350
We have victory!

2046
03:22:40,517 --> 03:22:44,479
SAM: <i>But in the end,
it's only a passing thing...</i>

2047
03:22:44,646 --> 03:22:45,980
<i>...this shadow.</i>

2048
03:22:46,147 --> 03:22:48,525
<i>Even darkness must pass.</i>

2049
03:22:48,691 --> 03:22:51,402
<i>A new day will</i> come.

2050
03:22:51,569 --> 03:22:55,532
<i>And when the sun shines,
it will shine out the clearer.</i>

2051
03:22:57,450 --> 03:22:59,828
<i>Those were the stories
that stayed with you...</i>

2052
03:22:59,994 --> 03:23:01,746
<i>...that meant something.</i>

2053
03:23:01,913 --> 03:23:04,499
<i>Even if you were too small
to understand why.</i>

2054
03:23:05,875 --> 03:23:09,712
<i>But I think, Mr. Frodo, I do understand.</i>

2055
03:23:09,879 --> 03:23:11,464
<i>I know now.</i>

2056
03:23:12,298 --> 03:23:14,509
Folk in those stories...

2057
03:23:14,676 --> 03:23:18,805
...had lots of chances of turning back,
only they didn't.

2058
03:23:18,972 --> 03:23:21,224
They kept going...

2059
03:23:21,891 --> 03:23:25,145
...because they were holding
on to something.

2060
03:23:26,729 --> 03:23:29,065
What are we holding on to, Sam?

2061
03:23:40,994 --> 03:23:44,914
That there's some good
in this world, Mr. Frodo.

2062
03:23:45,206 --> 03:23:47,834
And it's worth fighting for.

2063
03:24:14,736 --> 03:24:19,032
I think at last we understand one another,
Frodo Baggins.

2064
03:24:19,782 --> 03:24:23,745
You know the laws of our country,
the laws of your father.

2065
03:24:23,912 --> 03:24:26,122
If you let them go,
your life will be forfeit.

2066
03:24:30,460 --> 03:24:31,878
Then it is forfeit.

2067
03:24:34,631 --> 03:24:36,424
Release them.

2068
03:24:45,183 --> 03:24:47,894
[HOOVES BEATING]

2069
03:24:48,478 --> 03:24:50,521
EOMER:
Stay out of the forest!

2070
03:24:50,688 --> 03:24:52,482
Keep away from the trees!

2071
03:25:15,713 --> 03:25:19,801
[SCREAMING AND YELLING]

2072
03:25:43,324 --> 03:25:45,118
Final count...

2073
03:25:45,285 --> 03:25:48,204
-.. .42.
-Forty-two?

2074
03:25:48,371 --> 03:25:54,419
Oh, that's not bad for a pointy-eared
Elvish princeling.

2075
03:25:55,211 --> 03:25:58,881
I myself am sitting pretty on 43.

2076
03:26:03,011 --> 03:26:06,306
-Forty-three.
-He was already dead.

2077
03:26:07,056 --> 03:26:09,559
-He was twitching.
-He was twitching...

2078
03:26:09,726 --> 03:26:14,355
...because he's got my ax
embedded in his nervous system!

2079
03:26:16,649 --> 03:26:21,362
MERRY: He doesn't look happy, does he?
PIPPIN: Not too happy at all, Merry.

2080
03:26:21,612 --> 03:26:25,158
Still, I suppose the view
would be quite nice from up there.

2081
03:26:25,325 --> 03:26:28,286
Oh, yes. It's a quality establishment.

2082
03:26:28,453 --> 03:26:31,289
I hear the staff are very good.

2083
03:26:36,961 --> 03:26:39,339
-What are you doing?
-Nothing.

2084
03:26:39,505 --> 03:26:43,760
-The world's back to normal, that's all.
-No, it isn't.

2085
03:26:43,926 --> 03:26:45,178
I'm starving.

2086
03:26:45,345 --> 03:26:48,431
Good luck trying to find something
decent around here.

2087
03:26:48,598 --> 03:26:51,684
Probably dead rats and moldy bread.

2088
03:27:15,625 --> 03:27:18,044
Saruman's storeroom!

2089
03:27:20,380 --> 03:27:23,132
I don't believe it.

2090
03:27:23,299 --> 03:27:25,343
It can't be.

2091
03:27:25,968 --> 03:27:28,846
-It is!
-Longbottom Leaf.

2092
03:27:30,139 --> 03:27:32,475
The finest pipe-weed in South Farthing.

2093
03:27:32,809 --> 03:27:35,937
It's perfect. One barrel each.

2094
03:27:36,104 --> 03:27:37,230
Wait.

2095
03:27:37,980 --> 03:27:39,190
Do you think we should share it
with Treebeard?

2096
03:27:39,357 --> 03:27:40,900
Share it?

2097
03:27:42,735 --> 03:27:45,154
No. No.

2098
03:27:46,656 --> 03:27:47,990
Dead plant and all that.

2099
03:27:48,408 --> 03:27:50,576
Don't think he'd understand.

2100
03:27:51,828 --> 03:27:54,038
Could be a distant relative.

2101
03:27:54,831 --> 03:27:57,333
I get it.

2102
03:27:57,500 --> 03:28:00,336
Don't be hasty.

2103
03:28:01,421 --> 03:28:03,172
Exactly.

2104
03:28:04,257 --> 03:28:06,509
Bar—h rum.

2105
03:28:08,344 --> 03:28:10,346
[HOBBITS LAUGHING]

2106
03:28:32,160 --> 03:28:33,453
This is the old sewer.

2107
03:28:33,619 --> 03:28:36,747
Runs right under the river
through to the edge of the city.

2108
03:28:36,914 --> 03:28:38,666
You'll find cover in the woods there.

2109
03:28:39,709 --> 03:28:42,211
Captain Faramir...

2110
03:28:42,837 --> 03:28:44,672
...you have shown your quality, sir.

2111
03:28:47,175 --> 03:28:48,468
The very highest.

2112
03:28:48,968 --> 03:28:51,596
The Shire must truly be a great realm,
Master Gamgee...

2113
03:28:51,762 --> 03:28:54,724
...where gardeners are held in high honor.

2114
03:28:55,892 --> 03:28:57,894
What road will you take
once you reach the woods?

2115
03:28:58,478 --> 03:29:00,062
GOLLUM says there's a path...

2116
03:29:00,229 --> 03:29:04,150
...near Minas Morgul
that climbs up into the mountains.

2117
03:29:04,609 --> 03:29:06,360
Cirith Ungol?

2118
03:29:09,906 --> 03:29:12,450
-Is that its name?
-No.

2119
03:29:12,617 --> 03:29:14,285
No!

2120
03:29:15,119 --> 03:29:18,122
-Yes.
-Frodo...

2121
03:29:18,498 --> 03:29:22,043
...they say a dark terror dwells
in the passes above Minas Morgul.

2122
03:29:22,919 --> 03:29:25,463
-You cannot go that way.
SMEAGOL: It is the only way.

2123
03:29:25,796 --> 03:29:32,094
Master says we must go to Mordor,
so we must try.

2124
03:29:33,596 --> 03:29:35,389
I must.

2125
03:29:38,935 --> 03:29:42,522
Go, Frodo.
Go with the goodwill of all Men.

2126
03:29:42,688 --> 03:29:44,732
Thank you.

2127
03:29:56,536 --> 03:30:00,665
May death find you quickly
if you bring them to harm.

2128
03:30:13,135 --> 03:30:14,679
SAM:
Come on, keep up.

2129
03:30:18,140 --> 03:30:20,935
Mr. Frodo didn't mean for them Rangers
to hurt you.

2130
03:30:21,561 --> 03:30:23,396
You know that, don't you?

2131
03:30:24,188 --> 03:30:25,773
He was trying to save you, see?

2132
03:30:26,274 --> 03:30:27,817
Save me?

2133
03:30:28,150 --> 03:30:30,319
So there's no hard feelings.

2134
03:30:30,486 --> 03:30:35,616
-Forgive and forget.
-No, no, no hard feelings.

2135
03:30:35,783 --> 03:30:38,411
GOLLUM, GOLLUM.

2136
03:30:39,453 --> 03:30:41,205
Nice master.

2137
03:30:42,290 --> 03:30:45,126
-Nice Hobbits.
SAM: Very decent of you.

2138
03:30:45,293 --> 03:30:47,587
Very decent, indeed, GOLLUM.

2139
03:30:53,092 --> 03:30:58,306
Sauron's wrath will be terrible,
his retribution swift.

2140
03:31:00,099 --> 03:31:03,436
[RUMBLING]

2141
03:31:05,438 --> 03:31:08,441
GANDALF:
The battle for Helm's Deep is over.

2142
03:31:09,108 --> 03:31:12,653
The battle for Middle-earth
is about to begin.

2143
03:31:17,783 --> 03:31:21,203
All our hopes now lie
with two little Hobbits...

2144
03:31:22,204 --> 03:31:25,416
<i>...somewhere in the wilderness.</i>

2145
03:31:28,711 --> 03:31:32,131
I wonder if we'll ever be
put into songs or tales.

2146
03:31:32,298 --> 03:31:33,674
What?

2147
03:31:33,841 --> 03:31:37,803
I wonder if people will ever say,
"Let's hear about Frodo and the Ring."

2148
03:31:37,970 --> 03:31:41,223
And they'll say,
"Yes! That's one of my favorite stories."

2149
03:31:41,390 --> 03:31:44,352
"Frodo was really courageous,
wasn't he, Dad?"

2150
03:31:44,518 --> 03:31:46,187
"Yes, my boy.

2151
03:31:46,354 --> 03:31:50,149
The most famousest of Hobbits.
And that's saying a lot."

2152
03:31:50,316 --> 03:31:52,860
Well, you've left out
one of the chief characters:

2153
03:31:53,027 --> 03:31:54,904
"Samwise the Brave."

2154
03:31:55,071 --> 03:31:57,823
I want to hear more about Sam.

2155
03:32:02,119 --> 03:32:05,122
Frodo wouldn't have got far
without Sam.

2156
03:32:06,457 --> 03:32:10,503
Now, Mr. Frodo, you shouldn't make fun.
I was being serious.

2157
03:32:11,587 --> 03:32:12,963
So was I.

2158
03:32:21,847 --> 03:32:24,558
"Samwise the Brave."

2159
03:32:28,813 --> 03:32:30,147
FRODO:
Sméagol?

2160
03:32:30,314 --> 03:32:33,234
SAM: We're not going to wait for you.
Come on.

2161
03:32:33,401 --> 03:32:35,319
Master.

2162
03:32:35,486 --> 03:32:38,447
Master looks after us.

2163
03:32:39,240 --> 03:32:42,034
Master wouldn't hurt us.

2164
03:32:42,201 --> 03:32:44,662
GOLLUM:
Master broke his promise.

2165
03:32:44,829 --> 03:32:46,997
SMEAGOL:
Don't ask Sméagol.

2166
03:32:47,164 --> 03:32:50,376
Poor, poor Sméagol.

2167
03:32:50,543 --> 03:32:53,379
Master betrayed us.

2168
03:32:53,546 --> 03:32:56,632
Wicked. Tricksy. False.

2169
03:32:56,799 --> 03:33:00,720
We ought to wring
his filthy little neck.

2170
03:33:00,886 --> 03:33:03,639
Kill him! Kill him!

2171
03:33:03,806 --> 03:33:05,307
Kill them both!

2172
03:33:05,474 --> 03:33:09,103
And then we take the precious...

2173
03:33:09,270 --> 03:33:12,815
...and we be the master!

2174
03:33:13,482 --> 03:33:16,152
But the fat Hobbit, he knows.

2175
03:33:16,318 --> 03:33:18,988
Eyes always watching.

2176
03:33:19,155 --> 03:33:22,700
Then we stabs them out.

2177
03:33:22,867 --> 03:33:27,371
Put out his e yeses
and make him crawl.

2178
03:33:27,538 --> 03:33:31,000
Yes. Yes. Yes.

2179
03:33:31,167 --> 03:33:33,878
Kill them both.

2180
03:33:34,044 --> 03:33:36,547
Yes. No! No!

2181
03:33:36,714 --> 03:33:40,426
It's too risky. It's too risky.

2182
03:33:41,135 --> 03:33:43,721
SAM:
Where is he? Where has he gone?

2183
03:33:43,888 --> 03:33:46,515
-Hey, GOLLUM! Where are you?
FRODO: Sméagol?

2184
03:33:46,682 --> 03:33:52,062
We could let her do it.

2185
03:33:53,022 --> 03:33:57,193
Yes. She could do it.

2186
03:33:57,359 --> 03:34:01,906
Yes, precious, she could.

2187
03:34:02,072 --> 03:34:08,120
And then we takes it
once they're dead.

2188
03:34:09,038 --> 03:34:10,790
Once they're dead.

2189
03:34:10,956 --> 03:34:12,958
Shh.

2190
03:34:16,295 --> 03:34:20,007
Come on, Hobbits. Long ways to go yet.

2191
03:34:20,174 --> 03:34:22,218
Sméagol will show you the way.

2192
03:34:22,384 --> 03:34:24,637
Follow me.

2193
03:34:43,072 --> 03:34:45,991
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

